(159, 1, '2016-11-12 07:58:20', '2016-11-12 07:58:20', '<b>webks</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nHello, please tell to the ticket: BIGYU5K58A3256 From 4 days 0 contact.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nIt has been replied.', 'Tell to the Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'tell-to-the-ticket', '', '', '2016-11-12 07:58:20', '2016-11-12 07:58:20', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=159', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(161, 1, '2016-11-12 08:00:21', '2016-11-12 08:00:21', '<b>m2farma</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nHello, could you tell us when will next version be avaiable?\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nHi, its taking time, will try to release the new version this month.', 'Next Version', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'next-version', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:00:21', '2016-11-12 08:00:21', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=161', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(163, 1, '2016-11-12 08:01:59', '2016-11-12 08:01:59', '<b>nouredin</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nI’m wondering if I can create a new ticket in php code and fill it with specific data.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nCan you give us a example on how you are planning to do that.\n\n` This app is based on AngularJS and uses WordPress as a medium to manage content.\n\nThe Tickets are custom post type and the replies to the tickets are the commnens on that post type.\n\nHope this info helps a little.\n\n<b>nouredin</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nI need to create a ticket automatically when a user registers a new account containing his/her name and some information.\n\nIt would be great if you have an API or similar stuff to do that.\n\n<b>nouredin</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nI can use a WP function to create the custom post type and it’s custom fields, but this won’t trigger other functions I guess (sending an email for example).\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWe don’t have a public API as of now but we are working on it.\n\nYes, it won’t trigger other functions from within the app.', 'New Ticket in php Code', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'new-ticket-in-php-code', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:01:59', '2016-11-12 08:01:59', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=163', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(166, 1, '2016-11-12 08:10:54', '2016-11-12 08:10:54', '<b>DJNume</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIs it possible to have conditional questions for the form. Lets say the person picks option A for the support, I want it to display Question #1. If he picks B for support, Question #2 is displayed instead.\n\nAlso, is there a front-end admin page – so I don’t have to give support ticket agents access to the admin panel?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol>\n 	<li>Conditional dropdowns are not available in this version.</li>\n 	<li>Agents does not need to access the admin area to manage tickets, they can manage everything related to a ticket via front-end like replying, uploading and downloading files, etc..</li>\n</ol>\nThe only case i think we would need to access the admin area if they want to change something in their profile as user management like login and registration, etc.. is not managed by our plugin.', 'Ticket Agent Access', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-agent-access', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:10:54', '2016-11-12 08:10:54', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=166', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(168, 1, '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '<b>prg</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nA pre-sales question if I may. Is it possible to set a tiered ticketing system with payment? Perhaps Free or Premium with different response times between the two?\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\ncurrent version does not support premium tickets however, this feature will be available in upcoming version.', 'Tiered Ticketing System', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'tiered-ticketing-system', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=168', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(170, 1, '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '<b>kempoist</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nPre-buy questions. 1) Is it possible to appoint a task manager manually? 2) Is it possible to make so that the manager did not see the administrator tickets or other manager tickets?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nYes, you can assign a specific Department and Product to a specific user to manage and he won’t be able to see tickets from other Products or Departments.\n\nYou can try our plugin before purchasing here : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/">http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Task Manager', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'task-manager', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=170', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(172, 1, '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '<b>wpeliteplugins</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nWhy i am receiving email in spam everytime user create new ticket or reply in existing ticket. what should the problem? am i missing any settings?\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nmark the email address as not spam in your mailbox and it will start showing up in inbox. There’s no setting in plugin and it does not control the same .', 'Spam Emails', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'spam-emails', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=172', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(174, 1, '2016-11-12 08:21:14', '2016-11-12 08:21:14', '<b>faat94</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nis it possible to make automaticly a new ticket if a client buy a product on a woocommerce shop? So if a client buy a product there should be automaticly a order ticket and at this ticket the admin should write something like for example your repaired phone is still in process or ready to pick up?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWhile this is a great feature, unfortunately this cannot be done in this version of the plugin.\n\nWe will add this to our pipeline of new features and hopefully we can include this in one of our near future updates.', 'Automatic New Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'automatic-new-ticket', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:21:14', '2016-11-12 08:21:14', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=174', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2016-11-12 08:26:56', '2016-11-12 08:26:56', '<b>faat94</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nis it possible to make automaticly a new ticket if a client buy a product on a woocommerce shop? So if a client buy a product there should be automaticly a order ticket and at this ticket the admin should write something like for example your repaired phone is still in process or ready to pick up?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWhile this is a great feature, unfortunately this cannot be done in this version of the plugin.\n\nWe will add this to our pipeline of new features and hopefully we can include this in one of our near future updates.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Automatic New Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'automatic-new-ticket-2', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:26:56', '2016-11-12 08:26:56', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=177', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2016-11-12 08:29:33', '2016-11-12 08:29:33', '<b>galaxy5</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nJust wondering if you have a timeframe on the new system\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\ntrying to finish it by end of this month or early next month.', 'Timeframe on the New System', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'timeframe-on-the-new-system', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:29:33', '2016-11-12 08:29:33', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=179', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(181, 1, '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '<b>janesheeba</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWe would like to have one admin account to which all the tickets should be assigned by default – both the tickets sent by email and submitted on site. The admin can then decide to which staff the ticket has to be transferred.\n\nPlease let us know how to set this up.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nTo achieve this, from our plugin settings page under Manage Staff menu:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Select the user(admin) as Support Staff (also select the user’s to which you wish to further assign the tickets) and a Fallback User.</li>\n 	<li>Then, click on Assign Departments and Products and assign All Products and All Departments to the user(admin) only.</li>\n 	<li>After the above points all Tickets will be assigned only to admin and then he needs to login into the frontend of the app and then assign the tickets to the agents he/she wishes to.</li>\n</ol>', 'Admin Account', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'admin-account', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=181', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(183, 1, '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '<b>friedenstaucher</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nis it possible to change the time format? I don’t need “2 days ago”. I want to show the real time/date like this “November 23, 2016 – 01:30 pm” for example…\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWe don’t have a setting for this in the plugin, however we can edit/customize the plugin to achieve the desired result.\n\n<b>friedenstaucher</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\ncan you tell me where I can edit this? I have bought the plugin with the username “werbekracher”... for your interests\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nCan you please create a ticket at : http://support.cssjockey.com/\n\nSo that i can share the required info with you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Time Format', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'time-format', '', '', '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=183', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2016-09-12 09:22:03', '2016-09-12 09:22:03', '<b>connectus</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>is this open source? We want the ability to link our database so user do not need to register again, to log a ticket?</li>\n 	<li>can we replied to existing ticket via email?</li>\n 	<li>can we get notification via email for new ticket, new reply from agent/client, ticket closed/re-opened?</li>\n 	<li>Does it have canned response?</li>\n 	<li>Does it required wordpress or can we install without it?</li>\n</ol>\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nThis is not open source but once purchased you are free to edit as you may as the code is not encrypted or anything.\n<ol>\n 	<li>You can reply via email but we recommend only to create a new ticket via email and the replies must be via logging in into the system.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, you will get all the notification and you can also customize the email text for the same.</li>\n 	<li>Canned responses are not working in this version, we will fix it in another version.</li>\n 	<li>It requires WordPress.</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;', 'Canned Response', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'canned-response', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:22:03', '2016-09-12 09:22:03', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=186', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(189, 1, '2016-09-12 09:25:26', '2016-09-12 09:25:26', '<b>   KPR</b>\n\n<b>  </b>September 2016\n\nJust bought, thanks for all your help Mohit and CJ!!\n\n<b>cjrupak</b><b>    </b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nThank you for considering and buying our product and you are most welcome.', 'Thanking', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'thanking', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:25:26', '2016-09-12 09:25:26', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=189', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(191, 1, '2016-09-12 09:27:01', '2016-09-12 09:27:01', '<b>royalde</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nI have three issues.\n\nFirst: I would like know if it’s possible to sort products by hierarchy like:\n\nPants - Pants a - Pants b - Pants c\n\nT Shirt - T Shirt a - T Shirt b\n\nTennis - Tennis a - Tennis b\n\nOr if possible, would be even better, When select a parent category, show other select with products of the children category.\n\nSecond: When we transfer the ticket, we have to select the product again. It’s possible to leave filled, the product field in the ticket?\n\nThird: We need all the tickets are open to a specific User (manager / team coordinator). Is not good for us, tickets be randomly distributed among the users. Is it possible to set a default User to receive all open tickets?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nTo sort the categories/products we would need to customize or alter few lines of code in the plugin.\n<ol>\n 	<li>No, the product fields has to be filled each time but we will try and give this option in a future update.</li>\n 	<li>You can select a user for all products and departments by clicking on Assign Products and Departments button under Manage Support Staff menu. There should be only one user to whom all the products are assigned and then he can distribute the tickets to other agents manually as per need.</li>\n</ol>', 'Specific User', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'specific-user', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:27:01', '2016-09-12 09:27:01', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=191', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(193, 1, '2016-09-12 09:30:00', '2016-09-12 09:30:00', '<b>Probewise</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nJust bought the plugin. I’ve found a bug that purchase code can be reused multiple times, just tested it with your support forum with two user account I’ve created. I’ve also found out that you are using old API/Legacy API for verification, it might be good if the new API is supported.\n\nMay I suggest to fix this issue and add a feature that purchase code should be stored at the database. It would be nice if there’s a back-end list of purchase code of customers and support remaining months. Check this plugin: https://codecanyon.net/item/smart-bbpress-nverify/6370189\n\nI hope you could reply soon, because this is a big issue for Envato authors like me.\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nThank you for the feedback. We are implementing new Envato API with the new version (currently in development) and integrating more features as well around this.\n\n<b>Probewise</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nThank you for your response. I hope to see those updates soon, especially for Envato verification to limit license code per user and to monitor support remaining months.\n\n<b>Probewise</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nI just want to ask, when will the new version of the plugin be released? I haven’t use your plugin since I bought it, just tested in on localhost because of the bug/issue that I have reported one week ago. If the update will take a long time, it’s better to get a refund and I’ll use my old support forum system instead of your plugin.\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nthe new version will take at least a month as we are re-writing it from scratch.\n\n<b>Probewise</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nThank you for your response, hope to see the update soon.', 'Purchased Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'purchased-plugin', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:30:00', '2016-09-12 09:30:00', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=193', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(195, 1, '2016-09-12 09:31:35', '2016-09-12 09:31:35', '<a href="https://mzl.la/2cj9Vyn"> </a>\n\n<b>extensionforge</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nI set up Content Security Policy (CSP) and end up with that language file is not loading -&gt; http://bit.ly/2bXDbqN\n\nI set up the CSP with wildcart so everything have to load, but it doesn’t. Can u reproduse this issiue? CSP is necessary now so it would be great when u get into this: <a href="https://mzl.la/2cj9Vyn">https://mzl.la/2cj9Vyn</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYour support page is not working because you are using minifier on the support page like CloudFlare or something else.\n\nOnce you will un-minify everything, it should work. If not then please create a ticket at : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>extensionforge</b>\n\n<b>    </b>September 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI changed nothing on my setup only the CSP thing inside the htaccess. I only use google pagespeed on the server but it workes the whole time.\n\nI setup the question in ur suport-portal so we can go deeper into it.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCan you please get me the ticket ID, so that i can see if it has been commented on<b>.</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>extensionforge</b>\n\n<b>    </b>September 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nthx for getting back to this. I was on vacation, I didn’t start a ticket right now, but will do this week, when I made more checks with the problem.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>extensionforge</b>\n\n<b>    </b>September 2016\n\nthere it is: 3182\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nThank you. We have received your ticket and will get back to you as soon as possible.\n\n<a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/"> </a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b> </b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b> </b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b> </b>\n\n<b>    </b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Content Security Policy', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'content-security-policy', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:31:35', '2016-09-12 09:31:35', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=195', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(198, 1, '2016-09-12 09:44:15', '2016-09-12 09:44:15', '<b>seteoito</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nComments are not appearing on the panel, how do I solve?\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nPlease create a ticket at http://support.cssjockey.com with temp WordPress admin account, so we can check and help you with the fix.', 'Temp', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'temp', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:44:15', '2016-09-12 09:44:15', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=198', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(200, 1, '2016-09-12 09:46:32', '2016-09-12 09:46:32', '<b>newthink_iran</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nI have a question. Imagine we have several departments. When a user clicks on a certain button, I want to open ticket page and an certain department is selected, Without the user chooses it. Is it possible in this plugin?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nI am afraid this is not possible as of now in this version. Maybe we will include this in one of our future updates.', 'Open Ticket Page', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'open-ticket-page', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:46:32', '2016-09-12 09:46:32', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=200', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(202, 1, '2016-09-12 09:47:46', '2016-09-12 09:47:46', '<b>  schurikvs</b>\n\n<b>  </b>September 2016\n\nwhat must I do to make it all it is thus in the front area on German\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\n<b>  </b>September 2016\n\nYou can use any localization plugin like Loco Translate or any other you know and are familiar with.\n\nOr you can use any Software to generate .po and .mo files and place is under langague folder in our plugin.', 'Plugin Usage', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'plugin-usage', '', '', '2016-09-12 09:47:46', '2016-09-12 09:47:46', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=202', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(204, 1, '2016-09-12 10:03:27', '2016-09-12 10:03:27', '<b>TheChrisLusk</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nNot getting emails of new tickets now. All of sudden we just stopped receiving them.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nCan you please once get in touch with your host provider and have them look into the STMP server for any blocks or anything. Also ask them to check the email logs and see if they can find anything important for us to debug the issue.\n\n<b>TheChrisLusk</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nIts weird, its been spotty. Sometimes we get them now and sometimes we don’t. I will keep an eye on it.', 'Email Errors', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'email-errors', '', '', '2016-09-12 10:03:27', '2016-09-12 10:03:27', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=204', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(206, 1, '2016-09-12 10:04:42', '2016-09-12 10:04:42', '<b>webks</b>\n\n<b> </b>September 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>I have the ability to add your own translation? 2. The source code is open to change?</li>\n</ol>\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\n<b> </b>September 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>Yes, you can translate the plugin into any language. 2. The code is open. Once you are free to modify it as you may but the modification done by a third party will be out of scope in reagards to techncial support.</li>\n</ol>\n<b>webks</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>Whether the user can change their password?</li>\n 	<li>Can I add additional files to the ticket, microsoft word?</li>\n 	<li>Is it possible to increase the size of uploaded files?</li>\n 	<li>Is there any custom requirements of hosting a script?</li>\n 	<li>Is the script has an account administrator? It can create an account users?</li>\n 	<li>The script can be only one department that answers your questions?</li>\n</ol>\n<b>webks</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\n?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\n<b> </b>September 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>The user can change their password. As user management is not maintained by our plugin. Our plugin uses the user’s registered via normal WordPress register page or any other registration plugin you might be using.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, you can add additional fields to Submit New Ticket form.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, the upload size depends upon the size allocated to your WordPress.</li>\n 	<li>No custom requirements as such, just your server should support AngularJS and the JS and CSS scripts included on the support page should not be minified like by CloudFlare or any other similar service.</li>\n 	<li>The WordPress admin is the admin of the tickets as well. He as full right over it and also create a ticket on the behalf of a customer or client.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, you can create or choose only department who can answer the tickets.</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>webks</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nCool thanks.', 'Adding Translation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'adding-translation', '', '', '2016-09-12 10:04:42', '2016-09-12 10:04:42', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=206', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(210, 1, '2016-09-12 10:08:38', '2016-09-12 10:08:38', '<b>sarah23</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nVery nice and useful plugin. I am curious whether i can create more product along with Envato Item Sync.\n\nAdded Envato items but not able to create other custom product. Plz guide me.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nYou can create new products by going to Tickets and under Tickets section you would find Products.\n\nIt’s just like you add a category to a post.', 'Entavo Item Sync', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'entavo-item-sync', '', '', '2016-09-12 10:08:38', '2016-09-12 10:08:38', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=210', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2016-09-12 10:10:34', '2016-09-12 10:10:34', '<b>theme-plus</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nI’m want to integrate your plugin and WooCommerce plugin. Project is about selling Services.\n\nProject Requirement is :\n<ol>\n 	<li>Users select the services and place the order. (WooCommerce)</li>\n 	<li>After placing order, thanks page will re-direct to automatically created support ticket. Using their order input details.</li>\n 	<li>Created ticket should be private mode for that specific user(client) and our wordpress admin role(support agent).</li>\n</ol>\nI just want :\n<ol>\n 	<li>Creating private ticket using your plugin API. Just putting ticket title and content.</li>\n 	<li>Ticket created user and our WordPress admin users will see and access the ticket. All other public users and other logged users will not see this ticket.</li>\n</ol>\nI want to use your plugin as messaging system between me and my customers.\n\nPlease let me know, is possible with your plugin and how?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nAuto creation of ticket after an order from WooCommerce is not possible. Auto creation happens only from IMAP, where email received from the given email address under IMAP Configuration is converted into a ticket.\n\nAll the tickets are for private viewing between the admin, agent and the person who has created the ticket. Unless you specifically make the ticket as public.', 'Woocommerce Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'woocommerce-plugin', '', '', '2016-09-12 10:10:34', '2016-09-12 10:10:34', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=212', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '<b>piglabs</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\ndoes this use the wp login system for the logins? or is it seperate part of the angular app?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nIt uses the WP Login and Register system and in the plugin you need to specify the Login and Register links.\n\nYou can use any other login modules you wish to via some other plugin.', 'WP Login System', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'wp-login-system', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=214', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(216, 1, '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '<b>InstallationComplete</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nPre Sales Questions:\n\n1 – Can you create more than one link?\n\n<a href="http://screencast.com/t/kTLoOFNxdz7">http://screencast.com/t/kTLoOFNxdz7    </a>\n\n2 – Do these always open in a new page?\n\n<a href="http://screencast.com/t/D33qrtMgww">http://screencast.com/t/D33qrtMgww</a>\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\nOctober 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>No, we cannot create more than one link.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, it will always open in a new page.</li>\n</ol>', 'Creating Link', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'creating-link', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=216', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(218, 1, '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '<b>entavoaccount911</b>\n\n<b> </b>October 2016\n\nI cannot get the plugin to display anyything correctly it shows for example in the title bar\n\n{{lang.home}} {{lang.tickets}} {{lang.public_tickets}}\n\nsame on the side bar\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nPlease make sure that you are not using any scripts minification service on that page like CloudFlare or any other.\n\nThe JS &amp; CSS scripts loaded on the support page should be un-minified.', 'Plugin Error', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'plugin-error-2', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=218', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '<b>plabanm</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nis there a way to see how it works with woocommerce ? Please let me know. I need to know if it will serve the purpose before I buy.\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nYou can create a demo site on<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> and activate any of our products along with you can install any other plugin or theme and check the functionality.\n\nFYI: WooCommerce in this plugin is used only to sync the products added to WooCommerce so that those products can be listed as Support Products too. That’s It!\n\n&nbsp;', 'Woocommerce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'woocommerce-2', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=220', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(222, 1, '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '<b>m2farma</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nI would like to let people know, before purchasing this plugin, that the support is REALLY SLOW, taking more than 5 days to get answers.\n\nYou authors should tell about this at the plugin description: WE SUPPORT YOU BUT YOU WILL NEED A LOT PATIENCE', 'Plugin Issue', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'plugin-issue', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=222', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(224, 1, '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '<b>Robmason</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nPre sale question – How customisable is the New Ticket form? Can I have a large number of drop downs? Is there any way to have conditional dropdowns?\n\nFor example if SALES is chosen from a first dropdown, a second appears but sales based options, but if TECHNICAL is chosen from a first dropdown, a different second appears with technical based options.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nOctober2016\n\nConditional dropdowns are not a part of this version but it will be available in one of the future version, most probably in the next(upcoming) one.\n\nOther than that you can add other HTML field to the form which are single and multiple line text, single and multiple select dropdowns, radio, date, email and URL fields.', 'Conditional Dropdowns', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'conditional-dropdowns', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=224', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(226, 1, '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '<b>    webks</b>\n\n<b>   </b>October 2016\n\nOr maybe some new features will soon be introduced?\n\n<strong>c</strong><b>jrupak</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nYes, the next version it will be a complete makeover of what you see now, with much more added functionality.', 'New Features', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'new-features', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=226', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(229, 1, '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '<b>mistermuffin</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nIn several of your comments, you specify that Admin users can see and manage all tickets, even those which are not assigned to them.\n\nOn my side, as I am logged in as a Admin user, I cannot see all those tickets (front-end). How is it possible to change that?\n\nAnother question: where can I change (in the code) the automatic ticket assignment? I would like to assign all new tickets only to one specific admin user.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nTo be able to see all the tickets for a particular user on the frontend, that user needs to be assigned to all the products and departments created.\n\nYou can assign a particular user to all the products and departments by going to Manage Support Staff menu in our plugin settings and then click on Assign Products and Departments button.\n\nFollow this link for more info : <a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/managing-support-staff/">http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/managing-support-staff/</a>\n\n<b>mistermuffin</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nOK thanks.\n\nBut I just discovered one detail: if you want an Admin to see all tickets, you have to uncheck the option “Treat Admin as Agent”. If not, it doesn’t work.\n\nAnd what about my question about the automatic assignment? Can you tell me where to modify that?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nIf we are talking about assigning only tickets regardless of Products or Departments, then this is not possible but we can assign a specific user to any product or department and we can do that by again clicking on Assign Products and Departments button.\n\nAlso, please note that, If more than one user is assign to a product or department then the ticket will be distributed on random basis between the users. There is no way to control the assign of tickets itself to a user, unless you login into the frontend and assign the ticket manually from the right-hand side pane of the ticket window.\n\n<b>mistermuffin</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nOK, thanks for your answers!', 'Ticket Assignment', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-assignment', '', '', '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=229', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(231, 1, '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '<b>virteom</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nThe way our company is built is we have account managers that take the tickets first and then move the tickets up the chain. We don’t want the ticket system just assigning anyone random. We want to select the correct software engineer based on the ticket. So randomizing tickets isn’t helping us. We need to to be more like the tickets come in un-assinged and we assign based on need.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nAs you know, all the tickets are categorized under some Product or Department, so to assign the tickets to an individual you can create a specific Product &amp; Department and assign those to a specific user.\n\nElse, you need to assign all the products and departments to one or more users (probably admins) and then those users can login into the frontend of the app and assign those tickets manually to it’s respective users or agents.', 'Assigning Tickets', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'assigning-tickets', '', '', '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=231', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(233, 1, '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '<b>m2farma </b>\n\n<strong> </strong>August 2016\n\npre order doubt:\n\nDoes a agent can open a ticket for a customer that is not registered yet?\n\nCan a agent create a “customer username” so he could open the ticket and inform the customer that he can follow up at the ticket system, with the credentials x and y… etc..\n\nIm worried that my customers wont enjoy having to create a username in ticket system.\n\n<b>m2farma </b>\n\n<b> </b>August 2016\n\nHello there, just found out that i do can create a user for the customer, by typing his mail. Then he will receive infomation about login.\n\nThis bring me another doubt: the email that is received (that i mentioned), can i translate it? Will it come from where? I need it to be sent from my domain.\n\nCan i customize all emails that are sent to the customer?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes, you can customize emails send to customer and agents by going to our Customize Email section in plugin settings.\n\nMore info on this page : http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/customize-email-messages/\n\nIf you want to use our plugin and other products before purchasing, then you can create a demo site at<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> and use any of our products along with any other plugin or theme, if you want to check the compatibility with other plugins or themes.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Ticket Enquiries', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-enquiries', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=233', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(235, 1, '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nHow can we remove the “Starred Tickets”?\n\nScreenshot: http://prntscr.com/c2zpc7\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nWe cannot completely remove that but we can hide it using CSS.\n\nPlease enter the following CSS code in our Custom CSS Code section under App Settings in the backend.\n\n#tickets-nav .nav-tickets ul li:nth-child(3) {\ndisplay:none !important;\n}\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nThe css is work and also how can we remove the “Products” section in the sidebar?\n\nScreenshot: <a href="http://prntscr.com/c3t7x1">http://prntscr.com/c3t7x1</a>\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI set a custom logout url in SupportEzzy Settings screenshot<a href="http://prnt.sc/c4nson"> http://prnt.sc/c4nson</a> but when I visited the front end and tested the logout button it is not working please see screenshot<a href="http://prnt.sc/c4nu0d"> http://prnt.sc/c4nu0d</a> did you know why?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nTo hide the products, please click on ‘Yes’ for ‘Hide Products’ option under Basic Configuration in plugin’s backend.\n\nThe logout URL is not been properly generated due to localization, which plugin or method are you using for localization?\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes already click on “Yes” for “Hide” Products option under Basic configuration\n\nScreenshot:<a href="http://prntscr.com/c4qwzu"> http://prntscr.com/c4qwzu</a>\n\nBut still showing the product in the sidebar\n\nScreenshot: http://prntscr.com/c3t7x1\n\nNote: I am temporarily touch the code on your plugin to hide the product on the sidebar but is not life time fixed because when you have plugin updates the fixed will overwrite.\n\nNot sure about the localization but I think we use the wordpress core.\n\nAlso did your plugin can add more menu in here screenshot<a href="http://prntscr.com/c4r1i4"> http://prntscr.com/c4r1i4</a> and can add custom link? via basic settings.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nSorry for the delay in response.\n\nWe will check the Hide Product functionality and will fix the bug in our next version.\n\nYes, you can add more link to the menu by creating WP menu for supportezzy.\n\nWe have 3 custom menu locations: 1. Agents Only Menu (SupportEzzy) 2. Clients Only Menu (SupportEzzy) 3. Visitors Only Menu (SupportEzzy)\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI created wp menu for the supportezzy.\n\nScreenshot:<a href="http://prntscr.com/c98q6d"> http://prntscr.com/c98q6d http://prntscr.com/c98q6d    </a>\n\nBut there is no menu display in the site\n\nScreenshot:<a href="http://prntscr.com/c98q6d"> http://prntscr.com/c98q6d</a>\n\nDo you know why ?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nCan say without some debugging.\n\nPlease create a ticket at : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nTicket created.', 'Remove Starred Tickets', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'remove-starred-tickets', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=235', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(237, 1, '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '<b>frymde</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nCan i use the Ezzy plugin with WordPress 4.6 ?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes, you can use it with 4.6. We are not facing any issues with the new version and none of our customers have reported any known issues as of now with the new version.\n\nIf you face any issue, please open up a ticket at :<a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/"> http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n<b>frymde</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nOk. Thanks', 'Ezzy Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ezzy-plugin', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=237', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(239, 1, '2016-09-14 04:39:23', '2016-09-14 04:39:23', '<b>frymde</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI have a new question. If a client already send an email with a subject “One”. When a client send a new email with a suject “Two”, this email is generate as ticket update from subject One or in a new ticket? How is it possible that all history from the same client could be find in only one big ticket?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nIt would create a different ticket each time with different subject or email.\n\nIt is not possible to create a one big ticket unless all the conversation happens under one ticket itself. I mean we cannot group multiple tickets into one ticket.\n\n<b> frymde</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nOk. Thanks.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Ticket Enquiry', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-enquiry', '', '', '2016-09-14 04:39:23', '2016-09-14 04:39:23', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=239', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(241, 1, '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '<b>KPR</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nIs it possible to use a separate users table to keep it totally separate from the existing WP site..??\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nNo this is not possible in this version but we are trying to convert this into an API of it’s own using WP Rest API, so that it can be used on any or multiple sites with the same or different database\n\n<b>KPR</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nWill that be an update for this if i buy now.. Or a separate product..\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nIt will be the update for this now. Once you purchase a product the updates are free for lifetime of the product.\n\nOnly the support expires after a certain period.', 'Separate User Table', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'separate-user-table', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=241', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(243, 1, '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '<b>jonybigude</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nBy “Woocommerce integration” do you mean that previously registered users don’t need to create a new account because the support system works with the previously created accounts on woocommerce? And does one has to have the interface you provide or can one integrate it in a existing WP theme?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes, the users does not needs to create a new account if already registered via WooCommerce or any other medium, as our plugin uses the default WP users table.\n\nYou can integrate this into any theme you wish.\n\n<b>jonybigude</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nThank you very much! It seems that this is exactly what I was looking for\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nGood to know that.\n\nI would also highly recommend you to give it a test ride before you purchase on<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n<strong>On<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> you can create a demo site and install any of our product along with any other plugin or theme and test the compatibility and functionality of the product. </strong>', 'Woocommerce Integeration', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'woocommerce-integeration', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=243', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0) ;
