(264, 1, '2016-08-14 06:14:02', '2016-08-14 06:14:02', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>plabanm</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHow does it work with woocommerce ? please tell me in details as I am building a e-commerce main interest is that.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_14187203" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor woocommerce you can only export/sync the WooCommere products as plugin’s products, so that the user can choose the product they are seeking or support help for.\n\nThat’s all there is for WooCommerce.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Woocommerce Details', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'woocommerce-details', '', '', '2016-08-14 06:14:02', '2016-08-14 06:14:02', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=264', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(267, 1, '2016-08-14 06:16:37', '2016-08-14 06:16:37', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>Harlock_ </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, is there a link for every single SCR I can give to visitors for specific support about topics? Thanks, Francesco\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_14149153" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\nAugust 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes, you can give link for every SCR, just take a look at SCR in WP Dashboard.\n\nIt is basically a custom post type with a permalink of it’s own like any other post or page.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_14149168" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>Harlock_  </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOk, now I’ve noticed them. Thanks. Have a nice day, Francesco\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYou are welcome!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Link For SCR', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'link-for-scr', '', '', '2016-08-14 06:16:37', '2016-08-14 06:16:37', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=267', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(269, 1, '2016-08-14 06:36:10', '2016-08-14 06:36:10', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>maioona</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">if i dont have products i can remove this section? what about departments?</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\ncan i custm feilds?\n\nif a support agent is logged in, can he make a ticket on behalf of users? i dont see drop down menu, i must KNOW the name and spelling, is there a soultion for this?\n\nwhere can i see admin demo? in wordpress admin please\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_14187065" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYou cannot remove products or departments as those are mandatory for the plugin to work but certainly you can hide them from the frontend via CSS.\n\nYes, a support agent can create a ticket on the behalf of a client.\n\nYou can check and use our plugin by creating a demo site at : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Admin Demo', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'admin-demo', '', '', '2016-08-14 06:36:10', '2016-08-14 06:36:10', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=269', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(271, 1, '2016-06-14 06:49:37', '2016-06-14 06:49:37', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>timesoftimes</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nis it possible to create custom status ?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"><strong>cjrupak</strong></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291223" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nNot in this version but we will try and include this feature in our next version.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291234" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>timesoftimes</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nwhen we will expect ?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291257" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nProbably within next month.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291272" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>timesoftimes</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">i sent PM, kindly check it and reply me</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291296" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWhere have you send it, to what address?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291303" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>timesoftimes</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nsent via your profile\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291394" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOkay, that goes directly to the owner of this plugin. Would request him to look into it but that might take some time.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Custom Status', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'creating-custom-status', '', '', '2016-06-14 06:49:37', '2016-06-14 06:49:37', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=271', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(274, 1, '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>flyboy100</strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div>I bought this plugin recently and had a quick look at the code. The plugin is full of vulnerabilities!! Anyone can download any file from the server (depending on permissions), anyone can view all the tickets and in general anyone can do whatever they want. Even command execution can be eventually achieved. And all that without authentication! I don’t want to use this plugin any more, and want to request a refund.</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13332769" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>CSSJockey </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, can you please share the screenshots for such activity and also feel free to raise a refund request and we will process the same. We are re-writing this plugin from scratch with a bunch of new features and will take care of any issues reported by our customers.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Plugin Vulnerabilities', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'plugin-vulnerabilities', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=274', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(276, 1, '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>julianbazet</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, congratz for your great plugin.\n\nI really need to remove the following fields in create new ticket&gt;\n\nURL Priority\n\nAlso, I want to add some text explaining before the submisson of a ticket.\n\nIs that possible? Thank you!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13332209" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWe can hide those fields with CSS. Please create a ticket at <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a> and we will help you with it.\n\nSorry, we cannot add a text on the ticket page but we can add SCR’s and add some text on the homepage before logging into the system.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Adding Text', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'adding-text', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=276', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(278, 1, '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>frenv</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nPresale question: You say a user has to be registered before they create a ticket. But if they create a ticket through email, does this still apply? It should however. Example, I have a client that sends to <a href="mailto:support@mycompany.com">support@mycompany.com</a> – he should then get a message that his ticket has been created and he can “see it here” whilst me as the moderator get a email that my client has requested a ticket. That way he should not have to register right?\n\n- Also how is the SCR section working now? Is it displayable for non-logged in users yet? Also as someone said I would like it as a accordian as someone else said, you replied “Check the shortcode for SCR” but I cant find the information. Perhaps you could send a screen or something?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13332798" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes, the user will be created automatically if a user not already exists when someone submits a ticket via email.\n\nThe SCR’s are only displayed to logged in users.\n\nI would advise you to please test and use our plugin <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> before purchasing and see if it suits your needs or requirements.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'creating-ticket', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=278', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(280, 1, '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>joey41231 </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHow do i file for a refund for this plugin.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13349680" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPlease contact Envato for a refund as they handle all the payment related issues.\n\n<a href="https://help.market.envato.com/hc/en-us/articles/202821460-Can-I-Get-A-Refund-" rel="nofollow">https://help.market.envato.com/hc/en-us/articles/202821460-Can-I-Get-A-Refund-</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Refund for the Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'refund-for-the-plugin', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=280', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(282, 1, '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>Superwaz</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYour description says “This app does not interfere with your existing theme and plugins and will work with any kind of WordPress website”, but it doesn’t work with Avada as far as I can see. I could get it to work with more basic themes though. Is there anything I can do about this? Thanks in advance.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13349700" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCan you please tell us exactly what issue are you facing with the app or please open up a ticket on : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Plugin Issue', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'plugin-issue-2', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=282', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(284, 1, '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>TheChrisLusk </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIs it yet possible to actually get the data from the custom fields? Seems useless to be able to create a custom field, then not have it included in the notification emails right??\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13370976" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYou can create extra fields for Submit Ticket form and extra info from those fields would be included on the ticket page on the right hand side of the screen under Extra Information pane.\n\nBut those extra info will not be included in the Email Notifications. Emails only contain the necessary info and the link to check the ticket.\n\nRest, please check our Customize Email section in plugin settings.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13394490" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>TheChrisLusk </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThat’s the core issue here. Why would I need to create these extra fields and then NOT be able to get the data in the notification emails? A custom field should have a unique field name which should simply be used like the other fields… %custom_field % Maybe you even prefix it, but this seems to go hand in hand with being able to create a “custom field”\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13433018" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI would call it a feature more than an issue. Because you are getting all the necessary and required default fields in the email notification.\n\nBut we would give the option to include the custom fields in the email by customizing the email template from the plugin settings in our next update.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_14383026" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>TheChrisLusk</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">September 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nBOOM! And that’s why I like working with you guys, you are awesome! Definitely make this change because adding a custom field but not getting it sent to me (which is the purpose of email) is only halfway there.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Custom Field', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'creating-custom-field', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=284', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(286, 1, '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>DigitalMarty</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nJune 2016\n\nI read almost all of the comments here. I think I would buy this plugin if all the bugs and new features will be live soon. Any time estimation for the new version? – And also, 1. Is this plugin translatable to multiple languages, so client can choose his prefered language? 2. Is the integration works on any theme, or it works like theme and all I need is domain and..? Thanks, Martin\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13391539" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016]</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThe new version may take time to launch. That is why we decided to release a fix for some major issues that have been reported this fix release will be out by Monday or Tuesday.\n\nYes, you can translate this plugin into any language by using language plugins or creating po and mo files for the same.\n\nIt is a plugin and it will work with any theme.\n\nYou can try our plugin at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> . Here you can create a temp demo site and activate any of our products and install any other plugin or theme to check the compatibility before purchasing.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Language and Integration', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'language-and-integration', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=286', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(288, 1, '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>forester55</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\npre-sale question . 1. Already logged in wordpress user , when he sends a support ticket, will he be assigned a new username , password. ? I would like to have as a wordpress user should not be assigned a new login, password. 2. Can a useragent also reply to the email directly from his email client, instead of logging into dashboard ?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13473865" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n1. If a user is already logged into WordPress then we will not be assigned a new username or password or no new account would be created if he is not assigning a ticket on someone’s behalf and assigning ticket on a client’s behalf can be done only by admin or an agent given access to that particular product or department.\n\n2. Yes, we can reply via email as well but we strongly recommend to reply by going to ticket dashboard to avoid other clusters from an email like the signature and previous reply preview, etc.\n\nTry out our plugin before purchase at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Wordpress User', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'wordpress-user', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=288', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(291, 1, '2016-05-14 07:51:29', '2016-05-14 07:51:29', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>EvoRod</strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">May 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThe File Attachement doesnt send. i recive the email but without image .png and .jpg\n\nin case for (word) is doc ? correct ?\n\nThe Stars Rating doesnt work too.\n\ni have the last version\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13505295" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nPlease let us know the plugin version number you are using right now.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13508362" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>EvoRod</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nVersión 1.4.3\n\nThe attached file i saw when im going to answer a ticket on the sistem support portal, the attached file be on below the coment, but no recive too on the email notification\n\nthe rate star doesnt work too. i try on your demo and doesnt work the stars\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13535618" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIf you are using our latest version then these issues should not appear.\n\nCan you please create a ticket on <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a> so that we can securely share the website info and help you debug the issue.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Stars Rating Error', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'stars-rating-error', '', '', '2016-05-14 07:51:29', '2016-05-14 07:51:29', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=291', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(294, 1, '2016-05-14 08:00:24', '2016-05-14 08:00:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>bildraumwest</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHey, is it possible to embed google tables via frame in a “ticket chat”?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13509697" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>bildraumwest</strong></p>\nMay 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\niframe I mean\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13535663" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSorry, iframes won’t work in the plugin.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response"></div>', 'Ticket Chat', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-chat', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:00:24', '2016-05-14 08:00:24', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=294', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(297, 1, '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>mistermuffin</strong></p>\nMay 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThanks for this plugin!\n\nI installed it and have 2 questions:\n\n1. Is it possible to avoid new user creation (only accept tickets from users who are registered with their email address in WP)? 2. If not, is it possible to assign a ticket (created by an unknown user) to a WP registered user?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13535684" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nBoth of them are not possible in this version but we have this feature in our pipeline for our future releases.\n\nTill then I guess you can completely restrict access to the support portal only to registered users.\n\nDisable the email piping and let users submit a ticket and reply via only Web.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13559183" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>mistermuffin</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThanks for your answer!\n\nAnother question: is it possible to completely disable the “Departements” and “Products” taxonomies?\n\nEven if I hide them in the basic configuration, these fields remain visible and required when transferring a ticket to an agent.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13565847" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nProducts and Departments are necessary for the system to work. We cannot disable or remove that as this is a support app. Products &amp; Departments i guess are here to stay for long.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Assign a Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'assign-a-ticket', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=297', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(299, 1, '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">fusion</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI need to use this plugin only with my clients so I would like to create their user names and pass instead alow ALL users that access my support area. Is this possible my friend?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13535723" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYou can disable creation of tickets via Email and lets users submit and reply only by logging into the support portal.\n\nAnd on the left-hand side of the ticket screen just give a link to login and not register. I guess this should help you achieve what you are looking for.\n\nPlease try our plugin before purchasing by creating a demo site at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> and see if it suits your requirements.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13541012" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfusion</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThank you! How can I desable the Register Link?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13541304" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">cfusion</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nOps! I found it! Thanks\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604670" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCool. You are welcome!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Username and Password', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'creating-username-and-password', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=299', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0) ;
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` ( `ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(301, 1, '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">cfusion</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHow can I delete uploaded files from users? I think this is an important function. Thank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13546503" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\nMay 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOur recent update of this plugin has the feature to remove uploaded files. Latest version 1.4.3 also check the Upgrades &amp; Change Log on Item Details page of this plugin.\n\nRest you can also delete the file from WP Media section, if you know which file is it. As all the media gets uploaded to Media Library.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13547366" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">cfusion</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes I can delete the uploaded files from Media section. My plugin version is already 1.4.3 but a couldn’t find where is the button to delete an image uploaded directly on the Client Ticket (frontend), I coundn’t find this on your DEMO version also. I’m using Mozilla Firefox browser. Can you help me? Thank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13551898" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfusion</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI found it!! Very nice Plugin!!!!!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604664" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nGreat. Thanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Deleting Uploaded Files', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'deleting-uploaded-files', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=301', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(303, 1, '2017-05-14 08:34:02', '2017-05-14 08:34:02', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>wecanfixanything</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nCan you please explain awaiting response as its not working on this plugin and when some one post ticket it does not show anything on awaiting response.Is there any setting for this?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604659" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nAwaiting response shows the number of responses to be made on a ticket assigned to you or an agent. Each ticket opened by a client which has not received a reply shows up under Awaiting Response.\n\nIf a number is not showing up against it then I assume there might be a JS conflict somewhere, which we can only tell after looking the source code or checking up the console.\n\nSo, can you please create a support ticket at <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/.</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Plugin Error', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '303', '', '', '2017-05-14 08:34:02', '2017-05-14 08:34:02', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=303', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(308, 1, '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>GeniusLab </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"> May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIs there an option to ‘auto-close’ tickets that are already open for an X period?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604741" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes, there is an option to auto-close a ticket after certain days if there has not been a reply on the ticket from the client after the mentioned closing days.\n\nYou can set this option from our plugin settings under “Basic Configuration” menu look for “Ticket Options” section and specify the number of days after “Auto close tickets after” option.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13613608" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/GeniusLab">GeniusLab</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nAh – it’s already there, sorry I missed that! thanks.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Option For Auto-Close', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'option-for-auto-close', '', '', '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=308', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(311, 1, '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>j<a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/jerweb">erweb</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nis there any realistic date for new version as new version has been in the make for a while now and i am really waiting for it or should i better look for another plugin?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13632688" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/CSSJockey">CSSJockey</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, SupportEzzy will take some time however, new version for other plugins will be released within July.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13632962" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/jerweb">jerweb</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nother plugins? i was going on your statement that it would take about a month (couple of months ago) and have therefore not looked for other solutions. so there is no way for you to give an idea of when the new version will be ready?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Realistic Date for New Version', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'realistic-date-for-new-version', '', '', '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=311', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(313, 1, '2016-07-14 09:19:57', '2016-07-14 09:19:57', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>mike777 </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">July 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHow can i make the SCR public.. means users should be able to view without registering.. THX in advance\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13674471" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\nJuly 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf we talk about the in-built functionality for SCR’s in the plugin, then it is not possible to view SCR’s without logining in.\n\nHowever, you can give a link for you SCR’s page in the description on the homepage of the ticket.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'SCR Public', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '313', '', '', '2016-07-14 09:19:57', '2016-07-14 09:19:57', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=313', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(316, 1, '2016-07-14 09:28:07', '2016-07-14 09:28:07', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/extensionforge">extensionforge</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">July 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\njust for information. When I make a search-engine search and it shows the link to the support-portal the excerpt looks like:\n\n{ lang.quick_links }}. {{ lang.response_required }} {{ number_response_required }}; {{ lang.all_open_tickets }} {{ number_open_tickets }}; {{ lang.starred_tickets }...\n\nMaybe you implement a meta-description field or let is auto set the main-information.\n\nCheers,\nSteve\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13676895" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/extensionforge">extensionforge</a> </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">July 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">BTW: <a href="https://www.google.de/search?sclient=psy-ab&amp;site=&amp;source=hp&amp;btnG=Suche&amp;q=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.cssjockey.com" rel="nofollow">https://www.google.de/search?sclient=psy-ab&amp;site=&amp;source=hp&amp;btnG=Suche&amp;q=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.cssjockey.com</a>Here you can see what inside the desciption happens.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13701143" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">July 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThank you for the info. We will look into it and find a way to fix this.\n\nBest Regards, CSSJockey\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13701207" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/extensionforge">extensionforge</a> </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">July 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nGreat : )\n\nHave a relaxed start into the week,\nSteve\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Search-Engine Search', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'search-engine-search', '', '', '2016-07-14 09:28:07', '2016-07-14 09:28:07', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=316', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(318, 1, '2016-07-14 09:31:32', '2016-07-14 09:31:32', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/GeniusLab">GeniusLab</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"> July 2017</p>\n\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI’m going on my holiday soon; and would like my customers to know ticket response time is delayed due to that. Is there an easy of adding a notice on top ‘Holiday from .. until .. ’ for example. Or do you have another tip? Many thanks in advance.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13701334" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">July 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nUnfortunately, we do not have a holiday notice or response module in the current version but the good news is that this module is in our pipeline for future updates down the line.\n\nFor the now the best you can do is add some text in the Emails that are sent when a tickets is created or commented by customizing the email templates from our Customize Email Messages section in the plugin settings.\n\nOr, you can put a highligted text on the homepage of the ticket portal, when the user is not logged in.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Ticket Response Time', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-response-time', '', '', '2016-07-14 09:31:32', '2016-07-14 09:31:32', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=318', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(321, 1, '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/Elgunk">Elgunk</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nare you aware that these logins do not work? Technical Support Agent\n\nUsername: agentsupport Password: supportezzy\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12762857" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Yes, we are aware and we are working to fix this.</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Logins do not Work', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'logins-do-not-work', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=321', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(323, 1, '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/EvoRod">EvoRod</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">is posible to add or activate the widget plugin on dashboard wp-admin ?</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\ni have a book plugin and when i access to wp-admin dashboard apprears the next books and the activity of the plugin\n\nits posible with yours? i dont saw it on screen options\n\nbest regards\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12762861" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak"><strong>cjrupak</strong></a></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe don’t have this feature in our plugin as of now. Maybe in the later releases.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Add or Activate Widget Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'add-or-activate-widget-plugin', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=323', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(327, 1, '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nJune 2016\n\nHow to remove the word ” EMPLOYESS ” ...\n\nIn a support system the CORRECT WORD IS ” AGENTS “\n\nEmployees is for companies, stores, and malls word does not makes sense in a support system and look very bad there.\n\nPlease do NOT tell me to install LOCO PLUGIN it does not work or change the word\n\nThank You\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807882" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIf you wish to change the word and do not want to use any translation method then that can only be achieved by changing the word in the plugin files itself.\n\nOr, if you wish to simply hide the word then you can use CSS for the same.\n\nThanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807933" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWhat’s the CSS?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807945" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHere is what CSS means : <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_intro.asp" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_intro.asp</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807966" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI know what it means .. What’s the CSS CODE to change it .. your the developer NOT ME.. please read well i need to fix this,ASAP !!\n\nThanks\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808046" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n<cite>??</cite>...\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808130" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">\n<div class="comment__body--response"> June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOkay, sorry for the confusion. My bad.\n\nTry the following CSS code and paste it under our Custom CSS Code section.\n\n<code><span style="font-family: Courier New; font-size: medium;">\n#tickets-nav div:nth-child(4) &gt; h2:nth-child(2){\ndisplay:none !important;\n}\n</span></code>If this still doesn’t work, then please open up a ticket at : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a> and we will help you get a solution to the problem.\n\nThanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808175" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a></strong> <span class="e-text-label -color-grey-dark -size-s"> </span></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response"> June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">It works!</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808256" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nGreat!. You are welcome.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Loco Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'loco-plugin', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=327', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(330, 1, '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/dragonsflight">dragonsflight</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"> June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThe support tickets page keeps logging me out after 15 or30 minutes. Is there a way to extend this please?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12841405" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThis should not happen. As we do not have such a module in the support app where a user is automatically logged out after a certain time.\n\nThis might be a conflict with any other plugin or theme.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Conflict with anyother Plugin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'conflict-with-anyother-plugin', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=330', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(333, 1, '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/n1c0l4us">n1c0l4us</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello! Is it possible for the user to be able to submit a ticket only after making a certain amount payment? Or a custom solution to do this? Thanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12863184" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThis type of functionality is not built in to the plugin but you can restrict the access to the support page altogether unless a user is not a paid user.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Custom Solution', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'custom-solution', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=333', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(335, 1, '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/jerweb"><strong>jerweb</strong></a></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nhi, still wondering when the announced update will be ready..?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12892868" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThough we are trying our best to release an update as soon as possible but it may take a month’s time or so to make it public.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Updates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'updates-2', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=335', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(337, 1, '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/martin_basel">martin_basel</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi. Is there a way I can extend the ticket with additional fields I require?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976423" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Are you talking about adding additional fields to Submit New Ticket form?</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Additional Fields', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'additional-fields', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=337', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(339, 1, '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/JPednaud">JPednaud</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nTwo pre-purchase questions. I’m looking for something to be used interdepartmentally, not necessarily the client. Example, customer service requesting an it department fix a bug. Would this work well? Secondly, can I dictate was fields are required and what information is collected when oping a ticket?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976480" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n1. It can work inter-departmentally if the user is registered on the same site and you have created the appropriate department and product. The role of the user can be either customer or client but all this would be at one place and a common interface. You can check our plugin in action before purchasing over here : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> and see if it suits your need.\n\n2. Yes, you can dictate which fields should be required and which are optional.\n\nThanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13005004" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/JPednaud">JPednaud</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSo, I’ve set up a demo. But links to your documentation are broken. 404’s and dead. I can’t really fully test your service, unfortunately. That’s a shame, as I would like to buy.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13055597" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/CSSJockey">CSSJockey</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, sorry for the trouble. You can find the documentation at <a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://docs.cssjockey.com/.</a> We are in process of re-building all our products with current technology standards and security measures and all related stuff will be fixed as we rollout the new versions.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13058547" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/JPednaud">JPednaud</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSo this plugin isn’t secure or up to current standards? Okay. Thanks. I’ll shop around for something else. Thank you!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Working Interdepartmentally', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'working-interdepartmentally', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=339', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(341, 1, '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/demaiomassimo89">demaiomassimo89</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, it is possible change the color of the ticket, depending on your status? Such as those opened unanswered them green, open ones answered them yellow and red ones closed them. I mean maybe add a colored box next, as there is now for tickets unanswered. But it is also possible the possibility of creating the status “in process”? Thanks\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976413" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n\nThose color codes are not available in this version but it is on our to-do list for the upcoming update of this plugin.\n\nWe will also look into the In Process status too.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Changing the color of the Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'changing-the-color-of-the-ticket', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=341', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(343, 1, '2016-06-14 10:45:44', '2016-06-14 10:45:44', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/websitecenter">websitecenter</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, I have sent you a ticket regarding a few issues I have had with the software. the last response was 4 days ago, could you help me with the “No files found” issue. It seems to be something that happens regularly with the plugin from what I see in this comment forum.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976489" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSorry, it took time to get back to you but your ticket has been replied now.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Few Issues rregardd', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:45:44', '2016-06-14 10:45:44', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=343', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(345, 1, '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/websitecenter">websitecenter</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div>June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, I have sent you a ticket regarding a few issues I have had with the software. the last response was 4 days ago, could you help me with the “No files found” issue. It seems to be something that happens regularly with the plugin from what I see in this comment forum.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976489" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSorry, it took time to get back to you but your ticket has been replied now.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Issues regarding a Ticket', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'issues-regarding-a-ticket', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=345', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(347, 1, '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/Medhati">Medhati</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nwhat is your mean of envato integrated? when create a ticket must be fill envato filed? or if want register must be fill envato field?\n\ncan we required it?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12990145" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBy Envato Integration, you can check whether a custom has verified his licence of the product you are giving support to.\n\nFor this module to work you need to add your Envato Credentials in the plugin settings.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Entavo Integration', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'entavo-integration', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=347', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(349, 1, '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/Yolo-Themes">Yolo-Themes</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, i am willing to buy this plugin for my WordPress theme support system. But i cannot see how the Envato API Integration works. When will the user have to give his purchase code? I tried to create the system in your free all products webiste, but i cannot see where the user has to give the code. Thank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13055615" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/CSSJockey">CSSJockey</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, Once you integrate Envato via Plugin Settings, customers will have to supply their purchase code when they create tickets for your Envato product. Create a demo site at <a href="http://cssjockey.net,/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net,</a> integrate Envato and create a ticket as customer to see how it works.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Envato API Integration', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'envato-api-integration', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=349', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(351, 1, '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/EvoRod">EvoRod</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n<h2>Hi. why i can “rate” in the stars ? in the side bar</h2>\nTicket Information\n\nTicket ID: YZ4FFHM78D1720\n<h2>?????? Status: Open</h2>\nor what are the funtion of this stars? cause i click and nothing do.\n\ni imagine are to rate the answer of the support\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13119885" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThis is a bug, that we are going to rectify it in the next version of this plugin.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Ticket Information', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ticket-information', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=351', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0) ;
