(500, 1, '2015-12-19 06:25:55', '2015-12-19 06:25:55', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>Elnooronline</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">December 2015</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nCan I translate the backend and change to right – left ? i have wordpress in arabic can i make this\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_11371451" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>CSSJockey </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">December 2015</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, this functionality isn’t available by default and not tested. You can try the plugin at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net</a> and modify the CSS code via editor to see if it works as per your needs.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Translation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'translation', '', '', '2015-12-19 06:25:55', '2015-12-19 06:25:55', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=500', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(502, 1, '2015-12-19 06:49:44', '2015-12-19 06:49:44', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>hellobusiness </strong></p>\nDecember 2015\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, i have a problem with your system! When i press the submit ticket button, it is loading but nothing happens and stay there but the ticket has been created! It should move to another page, for example all tickets in order the user to know that the ticket has been succesfully created! What is wrong? How to solve that?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_11343034" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>CSSJockey</strong></p>\nDecember 2015\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, Can you please enable debugging under App Configuration and check if any errors shows up in Chrome Console.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_11343074" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>hellobusiness </strong></p>\nDecember 2015\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI get some errors: <a href="http://i.imgur.com/tI4wgXs.png" rel="nofollow">http://i.imgur.com/tI4wgXs.png</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-targe