(847, 1, '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>flyboy100</strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div>I bought this plugin recently and had a quick look at the code. The plugin is full of vulnerabilities!! Anyone can download any file from the server (depending on permissions), anyone can view all the tickets and in general anyone can do whatever they want. Even command execution can be eventually achieved. And all that without authentication! I don’t want to use this plugin any more, and want to request a refund.</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13332769" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>CSSJockey </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, can you please share the screenshots for such activity and also feel free to raise a refund request and we will process the same. We are re-writing this plugin from scratch with a bunch of new features and will take care of any issues reported by our customers.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Plugin Vulnerabilities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '274-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '2016-06-14 07:09:24', '', 274, 'http://127.0.0.1/274-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(848, 1, '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>julianbazet</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, congratz for your great plugin.\n\nI really need to remove the following fields in create new ticket&gt;\n\nURL Priority\n\nAlso, I want to add some text explaining before the submisson of a ticket.\n\nIs that possible? Thank you!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13332209" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWe can hide those fields with CSS. Please create a ticket at <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a> and we will help you with it.\n\nSorry, we cannot add a text on the ticket page but we can add SCR’s and add some text on the homepage before logging into the system.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Adding Text', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '276-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '2016-06-14 07:22:02', '', 276, 'http://127.0.0.1/276-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(849, 1, '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>frenv</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nPresale question: You say a user has to be registered before they create a ticket. But if they create a ticket through email, does this still apply? It should however. Example, I have a client that sends to <a href="mailto:support@mycompany.com">support@mycompany.com</a> – he should then get a message that his ticket has been created and he can “see it here” whilst me as the moderator get a email that my client has requested a ticket. That way he should not have to register right?\n\n- Also how is the SCR section working now? Is it displayable for non-logged in users yet? Also as someone said I would like it as a accordian as someone else said, you replied “Check the shortcode for SCR” but I cant find the information. Perhaps you could send a screen or something?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13332798" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak</strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes, the user will be created automatically if a user not already exists when someone submits a ticket via email.\n\nThe SCR’s are only displayed to logged in users.\n\nI would advise you to please test and use our plugin <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> before purchasing and see if it suits your needs or requirements.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Ticket', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '278-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '2016-06-14 07:26:40', '', 278, 'http://127.0.0.1/278-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(850, 1, '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>joey41231 </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHow do i file for a refund for this plugin.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13349680" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPlease contact Envato for a refund as they handle all the payment related issues.\n\n<a href="https://help.market.envato.com/hc/en-us/articles/202821460-Can-I-Get-A-Refund-" rel="nofollow">https://help.market.envato.com/hc/en-us/articles/202821460-Can-I-Get-A-Refund-</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Refund for the Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '280-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '2016-06-14 07:30:46', '', 280, 'http://127.0.0.1/280-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(851, 1, '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>Superwaz</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYour description says “This app does not interfere with your existing theme and plugins and will work with any kind of WordPress website”, but it doesn’t work with Avada as far as I can see. I could get it to work with more basic themes though. Is there anything I can do about this? Thanks in advance.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13349700" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCan you please tell us exactly what issue are you facing with the app or please open up a ticket on : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Plugin Issue', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '282-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '2016-06-14 07:34:51', '', 282, 'http://127.0.0.1/282-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(852, 1, '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>TheChrisLusk </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIs it yet possible to actually get the data from the custom fields? Seems useless to be able to create a custom field, then not have it included in the notification emails right??\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13370976" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYou can create extra fields for Submit Ticket form and extra info from those fields would be included on the ticket page on the right hand side of the screen under Extra Information pane.\n\nBut those extra info will not be included in the Email Notifications. Emails only contain the necessary info and the link to check the ticket.\n\nRest, please check our Customize Email section in plugin settings.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13394490" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>TheChrisLusk </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThat’s the core issue here. Why would I need to create these extra fields and then NOT be able to get the data in the notification emails? A custom field should have a unique field name which should simply be used like the other fields… %custom_field % Maybe you even prefix it, but this seems to go hand in hand with being able to create a “custom field”\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13433018" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI would call it a feature more than an issue. Because you are getting all the necessary and required default fields in the email notification.\n\nBut we would give the option to include the custom fields in the email by customizing the email template from the plugin settings in our next update.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_14383026" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>TheChrisLusk</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">September 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nBOOM! And that’s why I like working with you guys, you are awesome! Definitely make this change because adding a custom field but not getting it sent to me (which is the purpose of email) is only halfway there.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Custom Field', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '284-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '2016-06-14 07:38:16', '', 284, 'http://127.0.0.1/284-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(853, 1, '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>DigitalMarty</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nJune 2016\n\nI read almost all of the comments here. I think I would buy this plugin if all the bugs and new features will be live soon. Any time estimation for the new version? – And also, 1. Is this plugin translatable to multiple languages, so client can choose his prefered language? 2. Is the integration works on any theme, or it works like theme and all I need is domain and..? Thanks, Martin\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13391539" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016]</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThe new version may take time to launch. That is why we decided to release a fix for some major issues that have been reported this fix release will be out by Monday or Tuesday.\n\nYes, you can translate this plugin into any language by using language plugins or creating po and mo files for the same.\n\nIt is a plugin and it will work with any theme.\n\nYou can try our plugin at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> . Here you can create a temp demo site and activate any of our products and install any other plugin or theme to check the compatibility before purchasing.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Language and Integration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '286-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '2016-06-14 07:45:11', '', 286, 'http://127.0.0.1/286-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(854, 1, '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>forester55</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\npre-sale question . 1. Already logged in wordpress user , when he sends a support ticket, will he be assigned a new username , password. ? I would like to have as a wordpress user should not be assigned a new login, password. 2. Can a useragent also reply to the email directly from his email client, instead of logging into dashboard ?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13473865" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>cjrupak </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n1. If a user is already logged into WordPress then we will not be assigned a new username or password or no new account would be created if he is not assigning a ticket on someone’s behalf and assigning ticket on a client’s behalf can be done only by admin or an agent given access to that particular product or department.\n\n2. Yes, we can reply via email as well but we strongly recommend to reply by going to ticket dashboard to avoid other clusters from an email like the signature and previous reply preview, etc.\n\nTry out our plugin before purchase at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Wordpress User', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '288-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '2016-06-14 07:48:36', '', 288, 'http://127.0.0.1/288-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(855, 1, '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>mistermuffin</strong></p>\nMay 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThanks for this plugin!\n\nI installed it and have 2 questions:\n\n1. Is it possible to avoid new user creation (only accept tickets from users who are registered with their email address in WP)? 2. If not, is it possible to assign a ticket (created by an unknown user) to a WP registered user?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13535684" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nBoth of them are not possible in this version but we have this feature in our pipeline for our future releases.\n\nTill then I guess you can completely restrict access to the support portal only to registered users.\n\nDisable the email piping and let users submit a ticket and reply via only Web.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13559183" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>mistermuffin</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThanks for your answer!\n\nAnother question: is it possible to completely disable the “Departements” and “Products” taxonomies?\n\nEven if I hide them in the basic configuration, these fields remain visible and required when transferring a ticket to an agent.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13565847" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nProducts and Departments are necessary for the system to work. We cannot disable or remove that as this is a support app. Products &amp; Departments i guess are here to stay for long.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Assign a Ticket', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '2016-05-14 08:10:08', '', 297, 'http://127.0.0.1/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(856, 1, '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">fusion</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI need to use this plugin only with my clients so I would like to create their user names and pass instead alow ALL users that access my support area. Is this possible my friend?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13535723" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYou can disable creation of tickets via Email and lets users submit and reply only by logging into the support portal.\n\nAnd on the left-hand side of the ticket screen just give a link to login and not register. I guess this should help you achieve what you are looking for.\n\nPlease try our plugin before purchasing by creating a demo site at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> and see if it suits your requirements.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13541012" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfusion</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThank you! How can I desable the Register Link?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13541304" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">cfusion</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nOps! I found it! Thanks\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604670" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCool. You are welcome!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Creating Username and Password', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '299-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '2016-05-14 08:18:06', '', 299, 'http://127.0.0.1/299-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(857, 1, '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">cfusion</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHow can I delete uploaded files from users? I think this is an important function. Thank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13546503" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\nMay 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOur recent update of this plugin has the feature to remove uploaded files. Latest version 1.4.3 also check the Upgrades &amp; Change Log on Item Details page of this plugin.\n\nRest you can also delete the file from WP Media section, if you know which file is it. As all the media gets uploaded to Media Library.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13547366" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfusion">cfusion</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes I can delete the uploaded files from Media section. My plugin version is already 1.4.3 but a couldn’t find where is the button to delete an image uploaded directly on the Client Ticket (frontend), I coundn’t find this on your DEMO version also. I’m using Mozilla Firefox browser. Can you help me? Thank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13551898" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfusion</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI found it!! Very nice Plugin!!!!!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604664" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nGreat. Thanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Deleting Uploaded Files', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '301-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '2016-05-14 08:26:24', '', 301, 'http://127.0.0.1/301-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(858, 1, '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>GeniusLab </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"> May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIs there an option to ‘auto-close’ tickets that are already open for an X period?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13604741" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes, there is an option to auto-close a ticket after certain days if there has not been a reply on the ticket from the client after the mentioned closing days.\n\nYou can set this option from our plugin settings under “Basic Configuration” menu look for “Ticket Options” section and specify the number of days after “Auto close tickets after” option.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13613608" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/GeniusLab">GeniusLab</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nAh – it’s already there, sorry I missed that! thanks.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Option For Auto-Close', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '308-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '2016-05-14 09:06:22', '', 308, 'http://127.0.0.1/308-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` ( `ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(859, 1, '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>j<a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/jerweb">erweb</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nis there any realistic date for new version as new version has been in the make for a while now and i am really waiting for it or should i better look for another plugin?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13632688" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/CSSJockey">CSSJockey</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, SupportEzzy will take some time however, new version for other plugins will be released within July.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13632962" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/jerweb">jerweb</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">May 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nother plugins? i was going on your statement that it would take about a month (couple of months ago) and have therefore not looked for other solutions. so there is no way for you to give an idea of when the new version will be ready?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Realistic Date for New Version', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '311-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '2016-05-14 09:16:13', '', 311, 'http://127.0.0.1/311-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(860, 1, '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/Elgunk">Elgunk</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nare you aware that these logins do not work? Technical Support Agent\n\nUsername: agentsupport Password: supportezzy\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12762857" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Yes, we are aware and we are working to fix this.</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Logins do not Work', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '321-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '2016-06-14 09:36:12', '', 321, 'http://127.0.0.1/321-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(861, 1, '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/EvoRod">EvoRod</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">is posible to add or activate the widget plugin on dashboard wp-admin ?</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\ni have a book plugin and when i access to wp-admin dashboard apprears the next books and the activity of the plugin\n\nits posible with yours? i dont saw it on screen options\n\nbest regards\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12762861" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak"><strong>cjrupak</strong></a></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe don’t have this feature in our plugin as of now. Maybe in the later releases.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Add or Activate Widget Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '323-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '2016-06-14 09:39:40', '', 323, 'http://127.0.0.1/323-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(862, 1, '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nJune 2016\n\nHow to remove the word ” EMPLOYESS ” ...\n\nIn a support system the CORRECT WORD IS ” AGENTS “\n\nEmployees is for companies, stores, and malls word does not makes sense in a support system and look very bad there.\n\nPlease do NOT tell me to install LOCO PLUGIN it does not work or change the word\n\nThank You\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807882" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIf you wish to change the word and do not want to use any translation method then that can only be achieved by changing the word in the plugin files itself.\n\nOr, if you wish to simply hide the word then you can use CSS for the same.\n\nThanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807933" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWhat’s the CSS?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807945" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHere is what CSS means : <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_intro.asp" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_intro.asp</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12807966" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI know what it means .. What’s the CSS CODE to change it .. your the developer NOT ME.. please read well i need to fix this,ASAP !!\n\nThanks\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808046" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n<cite>??</cite>...\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808130" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">\n<div class="comment__body--response"> June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOkay, sorry for the confusion. My bad.\n\nTry the following CSS code and paste it under our Custom CSS Code section.\n\n<code><span style="font-family: Courier New; font-size: medium;">\n#tickets-nav div:nth-child(4) &gt; h2:nth-child(2){\ndisplay:none !important;\n}\n</span></code>If this still doesn’t work, then please open up a ticket at : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a> and we will help you get a solution to the problem.\n\nThanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808175" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/HendryRdz">HendryRdz</a></strong> <span class="e-text-label -color-grey-dark -size-s"> </span></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response"> June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">It works!</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12808256" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nGreat!. You are welcome.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Loco Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '327-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '2016-06-14 09:43:58', '', 327, 'http://127.0.0.1/327-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(863, 1, '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/dragonsflight">dragonsflight</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"> June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThe support tickets page keeps logging me out after 15 or30 minutes. Is there a way to extend this please?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12841405" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThis should not happen. As we do not have such a module in the support app where a user is automatically logged out after a certain time.\n\nThis might be a conflict with any other plugin or theme.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Conflict with anyother Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '330-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '2016-06-14 09:51:40', '', 330, 'http://127.0.0.1/330-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(864, 1, '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/n1c0l4us">n1c0l4us</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello! Is it possible for the user to be able to submit a ticket only after making a certain amount payment? Or a custom solution to do this? Thanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12863184" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThis type of functionality is not built in to the plugin but you can restrict the access to the support page altogether unless a user is not a paid user.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Custom Solution', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '333-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '2016-06-14 09:54:35', '', 333, 'http://127.0.0.1/333-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(865, 1, '2016-05-15 07:46:29', '2016-05-15 07:46:29', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>QualityMead </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">May 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nCan only registered users do email piping?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12219268" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>CSSJockey</strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">May 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nNope, new user will be created if the email is not registered in the system.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Email Piping', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '437-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-15 07:46:29', '2016-05-15 07:46:29', '', 437, 'http://127.0.0.1/437-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(866, 1, '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/jerweb"><strong>jerweb</strong></a></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nhi, still wondering when the announced update will be ready..?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12892868" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThough we are trying our best to release an update as soon as possible but it may take a month’s time or so to make it public.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Updates', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '335-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '2016-06-14 10:20:01', '', 335, 'http://127.0.0.1/335-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` ( `ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(867, 1, '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/martin_basel">martin_basel</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi. Is there a way I can extend the ticket with additional fields I require?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976423" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Are you talking about adding additional fields to Submit New Ticket form?</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Additional Fields', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '337-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '2016-06-14 10:31:05', '', 337, 'http://127.0.0.1/337-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(868, 1, '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/JPednaud">JPednaud</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nTwo pre-purchase questions. I’m looking for something to be used interdepartmentally, not necessarily the client. Example, customer service requesting an it department fix a bug. Would this work well? Secondly, can I dictate was fields are required and what information is collected when oping a ticket?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976480" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n1. It can work inter-departmentally if the user is registered on the same site and you have created the appropriate department and product. The role of the user can be either customer or client but all this would be at one place and a common interface. You can check our plugin in action before purchasing over here : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> and see if it suits your need.\n\n2. Yes, you can dictate which fields should be required and which are optional.\n\nThanks!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13005004" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/JPednaud">JPednaud</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSo, I’ve set up a demo. But links to your documentation are broken. 404’s and dead. I can’t really fully test your service, unfortunately. That’s a shame, as I would like to buy.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13055597" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/CSSJockey">CSSJockey</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, sorry for the trouble. You can find the documentation at <a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://docs.cssjockey.com/.</a> We are in process of re-building all our products with current technology standards and security measures and all related stuff will be fixed as we rollout the new versions.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13058547" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/JPednaud">JPednaud</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSo this plugin isn’t secure or up to current standards? Okay. Thanks. I’ll shop around for something else. Thank you!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Working Interdepartmentally', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '339-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '2016-06-14 10:33:24', '', 339, 'http://127.0.0.1/339-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(869, 1, '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/demaiomassimo89">demaiomassimo89</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, it is possible change the color of the ticket, depending on your status? Such as those opened unanswered them green, open ones answered them yellow and red ones closed them. I mean maybe add a colored box next, as there is now for tickets unanswered. But it is also possible the possibility of creating the status “in process”? Thanks\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976413" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n\nThose color codes are not available in this version but it is on our to-do list for the upcoming update of this plugin.\n\nWe will also look into the In Process status too.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Changing the color of the Ticket', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '341-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '2016-06-14 10:42:59', '', 341, 'http://127.0.0.1/341-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(870, 1, '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/websitecenter">websitecenter</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div>June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, I have sent you a ticket regarding a few issues I have had with the software. the last response was 4 days ago, could you help me with the “No files found” issue. It seems to be something that happens regularly with the plugin from what I see in this comment forum.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12976489" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nSorry, it took time to get back to you but your ticket has been replied now.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Issues regarding a Ticket', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '345-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '2016-06-14 10:49:15', '', 345, 'http://127.0.0.1/345-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(871, 1, '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/Medhati">Medhati</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nwhat is your mean of envato integrated? when create a ticket must be fill envato filed? or if want register must be fill envato field?\n\ncan we required it?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12990145" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBy Envato Integration, you can check whether a custom has verified his licence of the product you are giving support to.\n\nFor this module to work you need to add your Envato Credentials in the plugin settings.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Entavo Integration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '347-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '2016-06-14 10:52:00', '', 347, 'http://127.0.0.1/347-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(872, 1, '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/Yolo-Themes">Yolo-Themes</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHello, i am willing to buy this plugin for my WordPress theme support system. But i cannot see how the Envato API Integration works. When will the user have to give his purchase code? I tried to create the system in your free all products webiste, but i cannot see where the user has to give the code. Thank you\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13055615" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/CSSJockey">CSSJockey</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, Once you integrate Envato via Plugin Settings, customers will have to supply their purchase code when they create tickets for your Envato product. Create a demo site at <a href="http://cssjockey.net,/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net,</a> integrate Envato and create a ticket as customer to see how it works.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Envato API Integration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '349-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '2016-06-14 11:09:04', '', 349, 'http://127.0.0.1/349-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(873, 1, '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/EvoRod">EvoRod</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n<h2>Hi. why i can “rate” in the stars ? in the side bar</h2>\nTicket Information\n\nTicket ID: YZ4FFHM78D1720\n<h2>?????? Status: Open</h2>\nor what are the funtion of this stars? cause i click and nothing do.\n\ni imagine are to rate the answer of the support\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13119885" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThis is a bug, that we are going to rectify it in the next version of this plugin.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Ticket Information', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '351-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '2016-06-14 11:11:32', '', 351, 'http://127.0.0.1/351-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(874, 1, '2016-06-14 11:13:29', '2016-06-14 11:13:29', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/genloc">genloc</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, are problems with WordPress 4.5 known? Runs the ticket system with the new WordPress version?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13119646" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">We have yet to test the complete plugin on WordPress 4.5. We will publish an update if required and will update the info on Codecanyon that it is fully compatible with 4.5</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Problems with Wordpress 4.5', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '353-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:13:29', '2016-06-14 11:13:29', '', 353, 'http://127.0.0.1/353-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(875, 1, '2016-06-14 11:15:44', '2016-06-14 11:15:44', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/eddieneg">eddieneg</a></strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, after updating to new wordpress version , now the respond / answer option of the ticket is disables. Now I can’t answer or reply withing the ticket on the front end.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13119672" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe are testing our plugin features on WordPress 4.5. We will look into this problem and can you also please create a ticket for this issue on <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a> so that we can keep a track of the issue and keep you updated on the same.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13167546" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/eddieneg">eddieneg</a></strong></div>\n<div class="media__item">June 2016</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, have you solved the problem ??\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13173290" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a> </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWhile testing on 4.5 we have not faced this problem and we were able to respond and answer the ticket. There can be some other reasons that it is not working for you.\n\nOnce we get the info to your website, we will look into it.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Respond Option is Disable', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '355-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:15:44', '2016-06-14 11:15:44', '', 355, 'http://127.0.0.1/355-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(876, 1, '2016-06-14 11:21:06', '2016-06-14 11:21:06', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfu3i29</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nAny ETA on the new version and any list of planned new features available?\n\n- Will it possible to deactivate the creation of new accounts when new tickets are created from emails, i.e. to have them as “guest” tickets?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13134121" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfu3i29</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nAlso:\n\n- Will it be possible to alter the way tickets are distributed to agents? Random distrubution is not always desirable.\n\n- Can a “real” cronjob be set up on the server used to call the script that will retrieve messages from an IMAP mailbox?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13141111" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nThe new version would still take at least another month. Probably in this month or by the end of next.\n\nList of new features will be rolled out after the development of the new version is completed, as we got many updates and new features and we will see which ones are most important and which ones can be released later under minor updates on a regular basis.\n\nBut the features you have listed above will definitely be included in the upcoming version of the plugin.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13568321" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfu3i29">cfu3i29</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nDo you also have any plans to make it possible for users to access tickets created by email from different email addresses (i.e. separate user accounts for support users which allow multiple email addresses)? Reason: people often have more than one email address and don’t necessarily always use the one attached to their WP account.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13592889" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nNo plans to include this feature yet but we like the idea and we will try and make this possible down the road, as we proceed to elaborate this plugin and make it more and more flexible and customizable.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'ETA on the New Version', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '358-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:21:06', '2016-06-14 11:21:06', '', 358, 'http://127.0.0.1/358-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(877, 1, '2016-06-14 11:26:45', '2016-06-14 11:26:45', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n\n&nbsp;\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/timesoftimes">timesoftimes</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\ncan convert as a mobile app?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13186594" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Not as an app as of now but it would work on all resolutions as it is responsive.</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Convert as a Mobile App', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '360-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:26:45', '2016-06-14 11:26:45', '', 360, 'http://127.0.0.1/360-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(878, 1, '2016-06-14 11:28:44', '2016-06-14 11:28:44', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>afflabs</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nUsername / password for Technical Support Agent are still not working. Where can we test admin panel or get updated login info?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13251887" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\nJune 216\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWe are fixing the issue and by the time you can create your own demo site at : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net/</a> and in there you can activate all our products/plugins and also add any other plugin or theme and check that with our products.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Technical Support Agent', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '362-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:28:44', '2016-06-14 11:28:44', '', 362, 'http://127.0.0.1/362-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(880, 1, '2016-06-14 11:41:58', '2016-06-14 11:41:58', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>sandron</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nWhen trying to create ticket or viewing tickets, the right pane is blank for a logged in user.\n\nPractically the plugin is unusable for me. Created a ticket 20 hours ago. Didn’t get a response yet.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_13291174" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nOur support timings are from Monday to Friday ( 10AM to 6PM IST ).\n\nAlso, I can see that your support has been expired but still we have replied to your ticket today itself. Please check.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'The Right Pane is Blank', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '366-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-14 11:41:58', '2016-06-14 11:41:58', '', 366, 'http://127.0.0.1/366-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(881, 1, '2016-06-15 04:59:21', '2016-06-15 04:59:21', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>bagonline</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nIs there frontend registration / login for the user? I don’t want users going to wp-admin (wordpress backend).\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12398892" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"><strong>CSSJockey</strong> <span class="e-text-label -color-grey -size-s">  </span></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYes this can be done, try this plugin at <a href="http://cssjockey.net/" rel="nofollow">http://cssjockey.net</a>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Frontend Registration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '368-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-15 04:59:21', '2016-06-15 04:59:21', '', 368, 'http://127.0.0.1/368-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(882, 1, '2016-06-15 05:03:27', '2016-06-15 05:03:27', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>dtommy79</strong></p>\nJune 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nAny chance for adding support for easy digital downloads?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12398533" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>CSSJockey </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Right now we are more focused on upgrading the plugin. Removing any bugs and making it more stable.</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nMaybe down the line, we might try and make it compatible with other major plugins out there like Easy Digital Downloads.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Adding Easy Digital Downloads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '370-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-15 05:03:27', '2016-06-15 05:03:27', '', 370, 'http://127.0.0.1/370-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(883, 1, '2016-06-15 05:12:08', '2016-06-15 05:12:08', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>jeffgipson</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nI need help I submitted a ticket but no response yet… I setup up the plugin but I don’t see my logo or any content on the support page except placeholders any help on this ?\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12398455" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>CSSJockey </strong></p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">June 2016</p>\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0">Can you please mention the Ticket ID, so that we can take a look.</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'No Response', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '372-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-15 05:12:08', '2016-06-15 05:12:08', '', 372, 'http://127.0.0.1/372-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(884, 1, '2016-06-15 05:14:00', '2016-06-15 05:14:00', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>ericho09</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nemail pipe issue, when I use <a href="mailto:xxx@yahoo.com">xxx@yahoo.com</a>, it is 100% NOT create ticket. I tried two yahoo.com emails and both not working with no email received back from email pipe.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12420201" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cjrupak </strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nYou query has been answered on the ticket created.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_12440134" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>ericho09</strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted"><a href="mailto:helpdesk@cssjockey.com">helpdesk@cssjockey.com</a> doesn’t work for any of my yahoo emails too. Please help to check.</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Email Pipe Issue', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '374-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-15 05:14:00', '2016-06-15 05:14:00', '', 374, 'http://127.0.0.1/374-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(886, 1, '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '<b>mistermuffin</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nIn several of your comments, you specify that Admin users can see and manage all tickets, even those which are not assigned to them.\n\nOn my side, as I am logged in as a Admin user, I cannot see all those tickets (front-end). How is it possible to change that?\n\nAnother question: where can I change (in the code) the automatic ticket assignment? I would like to assign all new tickets only to one specific admin user.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nTo be able to see all the tickets for a particular user on the frontend, that user needs to be assigned to all the products and departments created.\n\nYou can assign a particular user to all the products and departments by going to Manage Support Staff menu in our plugin settings and then click on Assign Products and Departments button.\n\nFollow this link for more info : <a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/managing-support-staff/">http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/managing-support-staff/</a>\n\n<b>mistermuffin</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nOK thanks.\n\nBut I just discovered one detail: if you want an Admin to see all tickets, you have to uncheck the option “Treat Admin as Agent”. If not, it doesn’t work.\n\nAnd what about my question about the automatic assignment? Can you tell me where to modify that?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nIf we are talking about assigning only tickets regardless of Products or Departments, then this is not possible but we can assign a specific user to any product or department and we can do that by again clicking on Assign Products and Departments button.\n\nAlso, please note that, If more than one user is assign to a product or department then the ticket will be distributed on random basis between the users. There is no way to control the assign of tickets itself to a user, unless you login into the frontend and assign the ticket manually from the right-hand side pane of the ticket window.\n\n<b>mistermuffin</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nOK, thanks for your answers!', 'Ticket Assignment', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '229-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '2016-07-14 04:24:12', '', 229, 'http://127.0.0.1/229-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(887, 1, '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '<b>virteom</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nThe way our company is built is we have account managers that take the tickets first and then move the tickets up the chain. We don’t want the ticket system just assigning anyone random. We want to select the correct software engineer based on the ticket. So randomizing tickets isn’t helping us. We need to to be more like the tickets come in un-assinged and we assign based on need.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJuly 2016\n\nAs you know, all the tickets are categorized under some Product or Department, so to assign the tickets to an individual you can create a specific Product &amp; Department and assign those to a specific user.\n\nElse, you need to assign all the products and departments to one or more users (probably admins) and then those users can login into the frontend of the app and assign those tickets manually to it’s respective users or agents.', 'Assigning Tickets', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '231-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '2016-07-14 04:27:07', '', 231, 'http://127.0.0.1/231-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(888, 1, '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '<b>m2farma </b>\n\n<strong> </strong>August 2016\n\npre order doubt:\n\nDoes a agent can open a ticket for a customer that is not registered yet?\n\nCan a agent create a “customer username” so he could open the ticket and inform the customer that he can follow up at the ticket system, with the credentials x and y… etc..\n\nIm worried that my customers wont enjoy having to create a username in ticket system.\n\n<b>m2farma </b>\n\n<b> </b>August 2016\n\nHello there, just found out that i do can create a user for the customer, by typing his mail. Then he will receive infomation about login.\n\nThis bring me another doubt: the email that is received (that i mentioned), can i translate it? Will it come from where? I need it to be sent from my domain.\n\nCan i customize all emails that are sent to the customer?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes, you can customize emails send to customer and agents by going to our Customize Email section in plugin settings.\n\nMore info on this page : http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/customize-email-messages/\n\nIf you want to use our plugin and other products before purchasing, then you can create a demo site at<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> and use any of our products along with any other plugin or theme, if you want to check the compatibility with other plugins or themes.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Ticket Enquiries', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '233-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '2016-08-14 04:28:52', '', 233, 'http://127.0.0.1/233-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(889, 1, '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nHow can we remove the “Starred Tickets”?\n\nScreenshot: http://prntscr.com/c2zpc7\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nWe cannot completely remove that but we can hide it using CSS.\n\nPlease enter the following CSS code in our Custom CSS Code section under App Settings in the backend.\n\n#tickets-nav .nav-tickets ul li:nth-child(3) {\ndisplay:none !important;\n}\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nThe css is work and also how can we remove the “Products” section in the sidebar?\n\nScreenshot: <a href="http://prntscr.com/c3t7x1">http://prntscr.com/c3t7x1</a>\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI set a custom logout url in SupportEzzy Settings screenshot<a href="http://prnt.sc/c4nson"> http://prnt.sc/c4nson</a> but when I visited the front end and tested the logout button it is not working please see screenshot<a href="http://prnt.sc/c4nu0d"> http://prnt.sc/c4nu0d</a> did you know why?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nTo hide the products, please click on ‘Yes’ for ‘Hide Products’ option under Basic Configuration in plugin’s backend.\n\nThe logout URL is not been properly generated due to localization, which plugin or method are you using for localization?\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes already click on “Yes” for “Hide” Products option under Basic configuration\n\nScreenshot:<a href="http://prntscr.com/c4qwzu"> http://prntscr.com/c4qwzu</a>\n\nBut still showing the product in the sidebar\n\nScreenshot: http://prntscr.com/c3t7x1\n\nNote: I am temporarily touch the code on your plugin to hide the product on the sidebar but is not life time fixed because when you have plugin updates the fixed will overwrite.\n\nNot sure about the localization but I think we use the wordpress core.\n\nAlso did your plugin can add more menu in here screenshot<a href="http://prntscr.com/c4r1i4"> http://prntscr.com/c4r1i4</a> and can add custom link? via basic settings.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nSorry for the delay in response.\n\nWe will check the Hide Product functionality and will fix the bug in our next version.\n\nYes, you can add more link to the menu by creating WP menu for supportezzy.\n\nWe have 3 custom menu locations: 1. Agents Only Menu (SupportEzzy) 2. Clients Only Menu (SupportEzzy) 3. Visitors Only Menu (SupportEzzy)\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI created wp menu for the supportezzy.\n\nScreenshot:<a href="http://prntscr.com/c98q6d"> http://prntscr.com/c98q6d http://prntscr.com/c98q6d    </a>\n\nBut there is no menu display in the site\n\nScreenshot:<a href="http://prntscr.com/c98q6d"> http://prntscr.com/c98q6d</a>\n\nDo you know why ?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nCan say without some debugging.\n\nPlease create a ticket at : <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/">http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n<b>colourst</b>\n\nSeptember 2016\n\nTicket created.', 'Remove Starred Tickets', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '235-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '2016-08-14 04:32:48', '', 235, 'http://127.0.0.1/235-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(890, 1, '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '<b>frymde</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nCan i use the Ezzy plugin with WordPress 4.6 ?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes, you can use it with 4.6. We are not facing any issues with the new version and none of our customers have reported any known issues as of now with the new version.\n\nIf you face any issue, please open up a ticket at :<a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/"> http://support.cssjockey.com/</a>\n\n<b>frymde</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nOk. Thanks', 'Ezzy Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '237-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '2016-08-14 04:36:40', '', 237, 'http://127.0.0.1/237-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(891, 1, '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '<b>KPR</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nIs it possible to use a separate users table to keep it totally separate from the existing WP site..??\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nNo this is not possible in this version but we are trying to convert this into an API of it’s own using WP Rest API, so that it can be used on any or multiple sites with the same or different database\n\n<b>KPR</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nWill that be an update for this if i buy now.. Or a separate product..\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nIt will be the update for this now. Once you purchase a product the updates are free for lifetime of the product.\n\nOnly the support expires after a certain period.', 'Separate User Table', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '241-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '2016-08-14 04:43:19', '', 241, 'http://127.0.0.1/241-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(892, 1, '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '<b>jonybigude</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nBy “Woocommerce integration” do you mean that previously registered users don’t need to create a new account because the support system works with the previously created accounts on woocommerce? And does one has to have the interface you provide or can one integrate it in a existing WP theme?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nYes, the users does not needs to create a new account if already registered via WooCommerce or any other medium, as our plugin uses the default WP users table.\n\nYou can integrate this into any theme you wish.\n\n<b>jonybigude</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nThank you very much! It seems that this is exactly what I was looking for\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nGood to know that.\n\nI would also highly recommend you to give it a test ride before you purchase on<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n<strong>On<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> you can create a demo site and install any of our product along with any other plugin or theme and test the compatibility and functionality of the product. </strong>', 'Woocommerce Integeration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '243-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '2016-08-14 04:44:56', '', 243, 'http://127.0.0.1/243-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(893, 1, '2016-08-14 04:53:04', '2016-08-14 04:53:04', '<b>m2farma</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI want everybody here to know that the support after you buy is really really slow in solving the problems. Open your ticket and take a site because it will take weeks! I’m really desapointed.', 'Slow Support', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '245-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:53:04', '2016-08-14 04:53:04', '', 245, 'http://127.0.0.1/245-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(894, 1, '2016-08-14 04:58:07', '2016-08-14 04:58:07', '<b>szed</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nAnyone with a french translation ?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nSorry, we don’t have anyone for French Translation.', 'French Translation', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '247-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 04:58:07', '2016-08-14 04:58:07', '', 247, 'http://127.0.0.1/247-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(895, 1, '2016-08-14 05:00:18', '2016-08-14 05:00:18', '<b>BoRo85</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI have a pre-sale question:\n\nDoes your Plugin work with Buddypress?\n\nOn my Site I use the “Thrive Intranet &amp; Community WordPress Theme” with WP-CRM &amp; WP-Invoice, document management, etc. Is it compatible?\n\nI need a general overview of all interactions with the customer\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nThis plugin does not work with other plugins and other plugin’s shortcodes also does not work and here is reason why :<a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/why-other-shortcodes-and-plugins-dont-work-on-this-page/"> http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/why-other-shortcodes-and-plugins-dont-work-on-this-page/</a>\n\nHowever, the user’s registered by BuddyPress can be used in the app.\n\nHere is the list of all the features of this plugin : http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/\n\n&nbsp;', 'Plugin with Buddypress', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '249-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 05:00:18', '2016-08-14 05:00:18', '', 249, 'http://127.0.0.1/249-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(896, 1, '2016-08-14 05:03:18', '2016-08-14 05:03:18', '<strong>OdiGames</strong>\n\nAugust 2016\n\nI tried to read the docs at <a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/" rel="nofollow">http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/</a> but your site is down… get this message: Error establishing a database connection\n\nSame for the demo website.\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center">\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">August 2016</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">All that have been fixed now.</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response"></div>', 'Error Establishing a Database Connection', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '251-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-14 05:03:18', '2016-08-14 05:03:18', '', 251, 'http://127.0.0.1/251-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
