(937, 1, '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '<b>prg</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nA pre-sales question if I may. Is it possible to set a tiered ticketing system with payment? Perhaps Free or Premium with different response times between the two?\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\ncurrent version does not support premium tickets however, this feature will be available in upcoming version.', 'Tiered Ticketing System', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '2016-11-12 08:13:32', '', 168, 'http://127.0.0.1/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(938, 1, '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '<b>kempoist</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nPre-buy questions. 1) Is it possible to appoint a task manager manually? 2) Is it possible to make so that the manager did not see the administrator tickets or other manager tickets?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nYes, you can assign a specific Department and Product to a specific user to manage and he won’t be able to see tickets from other Products or Departments.\n\nYou can try our plugin before purchasing here : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/">http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Task Manager', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '2016-11-12 08:17:04', '', 170, 'http://127.0.0.1/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(939, 1, '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '<b>piglabs</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\ndoes this use the wp login system for the logins? or is it seperate part of the angular app?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nIt uses the WP Login and Register system and in the plugin you need to specify the Login and Register links.\n\nYou can use any other login modules you wish to via some other plugin.', 'WP Login System', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '214-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '2016-10-12 11:23:32', '', 214, 'http://127.0.0.1/214-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(940, 1, '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '<b>InstallationComplete</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nPre Sales Questions:\n\n1 – Can you create more than one link?\n\n<a href="http://screencast.com/t/kTLoOFNxdz7">http://screencast.com/t/kTLoOFNxdz7    </a>\n\n2 – Do these always open in a new page?\n\n<a href="http://screencast.com/t/D33qrtMgww">http://screencast.com/t/D33qrtMgww</a>\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\nOctober 2016\n<ol>\n 	<li>No, we cannot create more than one link.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, it will always open in a new page.</li>\n</ol>', 'Creating Link', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '216-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '2016-10-12 11:25:20', '', 216, 'http://127.0.0.1/216-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(941, 1, '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '<b>entavoaccount911</b>\n\n<b> </b>October 2016\n\nI cannot get the plugin to display anyything correctly it shows for example in the title bar\n\n{{lang.home}} {{lang.tickets}} {{lang.public_tickets}}\n\nsame on the side bar\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nPlease make sure that you are not using any scripts minification service on that page like CloudFlare or any other.\n\nThe JS &amp; CSS scripts loaded on the support page should be un-minified.', 'Plugin Error', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '218-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '2016-10-12 11:26:36', '', 218, 'http://127.0.0.1/218-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(942, 1, '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '<b>plabanm</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nis there a way to see how it works with woocommerce ? Please let me know. I need to know if it will serve the purpose before I buy.\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nYou can create a demo site on<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> and activate any of our products along with you can install any other plugin or theme and check the functionality.\n\nFYI: WooCommerce in this plugin is used only to sync the products added to WooCommerce so that those products can be listed as Support Products too. That’s It!\n\n&nbsp;', 'Woocommerce', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '2016-10-12 11:34:25', '', 220, 'http://127.0.0.1/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(943, 1, '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '<b>m2farma</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nI would like to let people know, before purchasing this plugin, that the support is REALLY SLOW, taking more than 5 days to get answers.\n\nYou authors should tell about this at the plugin description: WE SUPPORT YOU BUT YOU WILL NEED A LOT PATIENCE', 'Plugin Issue', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '222-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '2016-10-12 11:36:18', '', 222, 'http://127.0.0.1/222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(944, 1, '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '<b>Robmason</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nPre sale question – How customisable is the New Ticket form? Can I have a large number of drop downs? Is there any way to have conditional dropdowns?\n\nFor example if SALES is chosen from a first dropdown, a second appears but sales based options, but if TECHNICAL is chosen from a first dropdown, a different second appears with technical based options.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nOctober2016\n\nConditional dropdowns are not a part of this version but it will be available in one of the future version, most probably in the next(upcoming) one.\n\nOther than that you can add other HTML field to the form which are single and multiple line text, single and multiple select dropdowns, radio, date, email and URL fields.', 'Conditional Dropdowns', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '224-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '2016-10-12 11:37:22', '', 224, 'http://127.0.0.1/224-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(945, 1, '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '<b>    webks</b>\n\n<b>   </b>October 2016\n\nOr maybe some new features will soon be introduced?\n\n<strong>c</strong><b>jrupak</b>\n\nOctober 2016\n\nYes, the next version it will be a complete makeover of what you see now, with much more added functionality.', 'New Features', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '226-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '2016-10-12 11:45:51', '', 226, 'http://127.0.0.1/226-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(946, 1, '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '<b>sabaor</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI can not see the instructions for install the app. Your web is not working.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWeb sites are working now. You can look for the instructions.', 'Web Error', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'web-error', '', '', '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=92', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(947, 1, '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '<b>sabaor</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI can not see the instructions for install the app. Your web is not working.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWeb sites are working now. You can look for the instructions.', 'Web Error', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '946-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '2016-12-12 06:51:56', '', 946, 'http://127.0.0.1/946-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(948, 1, '2016-12-12 06:53:28', '2016-12-12 06:53:28', '<b>pcwd</b>\n\n<b>    </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nlive preview is down?\n\nAlso just wondering can this be placed within a page and still keep the wordpress theme header and footer etc?\n\nFew questions: 1. I there a link in woocommerce my account area for them to click on to get in to the ticket area? Or do i need to link to the page?\n<ol start="2">\n 	<li>If a client purchases something from my woocommerce store and then creates a ticket will it show me which subscription they have purchased and if it’s still valid e.g. subscription not canceled?</li>\n 	<li>I am assuming that users don’t need a different login from what they use to manage their woocommerce account?</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak </b>\n\n<b>    </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nLive preview should work now.\n\nYes, you can place the app within your header and footer, follow this link for more info :<a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/run-app-within-a-page-with-header-and-footer/"> http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/run-app-within-a-page-with-header-and-footer/</a>\n<ol>\n 	<li>For woocommerce all our app does is takes the products from woocommerce and list those products as products for support in the app. You would need to link it to the support page.</li>\n 	<li>No, it won’t get the info for the purchase history, right now we only have this feature for Envato products, if you link Envato to our app then it would show if the user is a verified user or not.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, no need for a different login, we use the default WordPress user database as well.</li>\n</ol>\nYou can try our plugin on :<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a>', 'woocommerce', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '94-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 06:53:28', '2016-12-12 06:53:28', '', 94, 'http://127.0.0.1/94-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(949, 1, '2016-12-12 06:55:23', '2016-12-12 06:55:23', '<b>    zOrg</b>\n\n<b>    </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWhen will be released the next version with VueJS framework?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI am trying my best to release this within this month, however, we have other plugins as well which are in development so time is a bit divided.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Next Version with VueJS Framework', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '96-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 06:55:23', '2016-12-12 06:55:23', '', 96, 'http://127.0.0.1/96-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(950, 1, '2016-12-12 06:59:03', '2016-12-12 06:59:03', '<b>gdaq</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWhat if the server does not have the option to email piping?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHi, php_imap extension is required to use this feature.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Email piping', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '98-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 06:59:03', '2016-12-12 06:59:03', '', 98, 'http://127.0.0.1/98-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(951, 1, '2016-12-12 07:00:08', '2016-12-12 07:00:08', '<b>RobMason</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nwhat’s the easiest way to change the ‘Select Department’ text?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>    </b><b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nUse loco translate plugin and change the text under translations.', 'Select Department', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '100-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:00:08', '2016-12-12 07:00:08', '', 100, 'http://127.0.0.1/100-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(952, 1, '2016-12-12 07:01:37', '2016-12-12 07:01:37', '<b>newpappa</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIs it possible for users to submit a support request by simply emailing a specific email, without registering and without logging in? Sort of like Craigslist?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\n<b>    </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYes, users can send an email to address configured under plugin imap settings and system will check if the sender email is registered or not, if yes, then it will create a new ticket under user’s account otherwise create a new account and create a ticket. Next time if the user reply to the agent answer, new comment will be added.', 'Emailing a Specific Email', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '103-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:01:37', '2016-12-12 07:01:37', '', 103, 'http://127.0.0.1/103-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(953, 1, '2016-12-12 07:03:15', '2016-12-12 07:03:15', '<b>thehotfix</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\nHow to add “Public Tickets” and “Private Tickets” – i see no option by create a new Ticket\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHi, only agent or admin mark a ticket as public/private. You can set default status from plugin settings.', 'Plugin Settings', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '105-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:03:15', '2016-12-12 07:03:15', '', 105, 'http://127.0.0.1/105-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(954, 1, '2016-12-12 07:04:50', '2016-12-12 07:04:50', '<b>m2farma</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI have a doubt you have answered before for another user, but it is not working:\n\nOther user question:\n\nWe would like to have one admin account to which all the tickets should be assigned by default – both the tickets sent by email and submitted on site. The admin can then decide to which staff the ticket has to be transferred.\n\nPlease let us know how to set this up.\n\n<b>Cheers, Jane.</b>\n\ncjrupak 18 days ago Flag Hi,\n\nTo achieve this, from our plugin settings page under Manage Staff menu:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Select the user(admin) as Support Staff (also select the user’s to which you wish to further assign the tickets) and a Fallback User.</li>\n 	<li>Then, click on Assign Departments and Products and assign All Products and All Departments to the user(admin) only.</li>\n 	<li>After the above points all Tickets will be assigned only to admin and then he needs to login into the frontend of the app and then assign the tickets to the agents he/she wishes to.</li>\n</ol>\nThanks!\n\nI tried to do what you said, the admin is set of he can see all departments, but the other users, they already have departments set for them. I can’t delete the department..', 'Plugin Settings', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:04:50', '2016-12-12 07:04:50', '', 107, 'http://127.0.0.1/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(955, 1, '2016-12-12 07:07:01', '2016-12-12 07:07:01', '<b>bris-emarketing</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHi, we are planing to buy this… but I would like to ask couple of questions before we purchase.\n<ol>\n 	<li>Email enquiry can be stored automatically in the system?</li>\n 	<li>If we nominate the person (agent) who need to answer the enquiry, the person (agent) will get the notification by email?</li>\n 	<li>If the person (agent) reply the email, the system will catch the reply and send the answer email to the customer directly?</li>\n</ol>\nOur staff doesn’t want to login the system. They only wanna answer the question if they received the enquiry from the website to their email inbox.\n\nCurrently, we are using Zendesk at the moment. Do you think this application can cover what we want? Thanks!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHello, Yes all this can be handled by this plugin. However, this system uses php_imap extension which process emails when the website is accessed or any page is opened in a browser. Your staff would need to reply from their dashboard within the system in the current version. However, the new version is in development and this will be covered as well with very simple setup.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>bris-emarketing</b>\n\n<b>    </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThank you very much for your quick response… That means if our staff want to answer the enquiry by an email, they must be on the program has been logged in?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYes, php will process all emails when the site is accessed.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>bris-emarketing</b>\n\n<b> </b>December 2016\n\nThanks for the reply. I have two more questions before we purchase.\n<ol>\n 	<li>Is there any function that the email notification will contain the direct link for the reply the enquiry? 2. Is there any option to login this system with the Google account?</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nEmail sent by SupportEzzy has the link to ticket and for google login you can use our Frontend Membership Modules<a href="https://goo.gl/1lM2GF."> https://goo.gl/1lM2GF.</a> I’d recommend you to try our plugins at<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net</a> and see if they meet all your requirements. Feel free to ask any questions once you try our products.', 'Email Enquiry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '109-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:07:01', '2016-12-12 07:07:01', '', 109, 'http://127.0.0.1/109-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(956, 1, '2016-12-12 07:08:35', '2016-12-12 07:08:35', '<b>vcdesigns</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\ni have left messages and replies to an open ticket that has been open now for a month and the information you asked for i provided twice and still nobody has done anything about this. Ticket ID: FMYQN0CC803302\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe really apologize for the delay and the problem has been solved and the ticket has been answered.', 'Unanswered Ticket', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '111-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:08:35', '2016-12-12 07:08:35', '', 111, 'http://127.0.0.1/111-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(957, 1, '2016-12-12 07:10:51', '2016-12-12 07:10:51', '<b>meken</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\nmy site suddenly run into blank screen, I think it is because of email piping: Ticket ID: UEF2BM89AA3407\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\nCan you please confirm with your host if Email Piping is enables in your server.\n\n<b>meken</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\nSure, runs normally for 1 day, dealing with some tickets, then suddenly blank screen, from the apache error log, I think it is email-piping. Disable it via phpmyadmin, it goes ok.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>meken</b>\n\n<strong> </strong>December 2016\n\nphp7.0-imap is already the newest version (7.0.14-2+deb.sury.org~xenial+1).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\nAlright, we are following the issue on the ticket you had created and we will look into this further.', 'Email piping', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '114-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:10:51', '2016-12-12 07:10:51', '', 114, 'http://127.0.0.1/114-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(958, 1, '2016-12-12 07:13:25', '2016-12-12 07:13:25', '<b>BLUEZMEDIA</b>\n\n<b> </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor the upcoming release, does the new version/framework work as the actual ? (cf. we do not call wp_head() and wp_footer() functions on this page to avoid any layout issues, javascript conflicts and most importantly AngularJS setup.)\n\nWill it be possible to integrate it in standard wp page ? Keep the header and footer and make your plugin compatible with others !\n\nIf this the case, then please consider compatibility with Buddypress.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\nAs long as display goes, we can still use the app with header and footer visible but the wp_footer and wp_head function are not called inside the app templates and we will try to make it more compatible with WordPress and BuddyPress too.\n\nFollow this page for more info : <a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/run-app-within-a-page-with-header-and-footer/">http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/run-app-within-a-page-with-header-and-footer/</a>', 'New Version / Framework Work', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '116-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:13:25', '2016-12-12 07:13:25', '', 116, 'http://127.0.0.1/116-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(959, 1, '2016-12-12 07:15:38', '2016-12-12 07:15:38', '<b>watechno</b>\n\n<b> </b>December 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI have a pre-sales question, when a client inputs his purchase code, will the system tell me if it is still a supported client or not ? because as you know, support runs out after 6 months on envato ..\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>CSSJockey</b>\n\nDecember 2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCurrent version is built with old api, however, new version is being developed with new api will check if support is valid or not.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Question on Purchase Code', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '119-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-12 07:15:38', '2016-12-12 07:15:38', '', 119, 'http://127.0.0.1/119-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(960, 1, '2017-01-12 07:18:16', '2017-01-12 07:18:16', '<b>colorlink2</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nwhen it sync woocommerce products , does it do it for each and every user request?! or does it sync by its own and shows result to ppl ?\n\nbecause over here its taking ages to open the page , after i enabled the sync .\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>`</b><b>    </b><b>colorlink2</b>\n\n<b>    </b>January 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nyour plugin made my server use up to 100% cpu , to sync woocommerce ,, why not just USE woocommerce products there?!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\nThe woocommerce sync happens whenever admin_init hook is fired, to check if there is any new product added or not.\n\nAfter it is first initialized, i dont think you would face such a high usage moving forward.\n\nHow many products do you have?', 'Sync woocommerce', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '121-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:18:16', '2017-01-12 07:18:16', '', 121, 'http://127.0.0.1/121-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(961, 1, '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '<b>wpeliteplugins</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nWhy i am receiving email in spam everytime user create new ticket or reply in existing ticket. what should the problem? am i missing any settings?\n\n<b>CSSJockey </b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nmark the email address as not spam in your mailbox and it will start showing up in inbox. There’s no setting in plugin and it does not control the same .', 'Spam Emails', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '2016-11-12 08:19:09', '', 172, 'http://127.0.0.1/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
