(965, 1, '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '<b>janesheeba</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWe would like to have one admin account to which all the tickets should be assigned by default – both the tickets sent by email and submitted on site. The admin can then decide to which staff the ticket has to be transferred.\n\nPlease let us know how to set this up.\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nTo achieve this, from our plugin settings page under Manage Staff menu:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Select the user(admin) as Support Staff (also select the user’s to which you wish to further assign the tickets) and a Fallback User.</li>\n 	<li>Then, click on Assign Departments and Products and assign All Products and All Departments to the user(admin) only.</li>\n 	<li>After the above points all Tickets will be assigned only to admin and then he needs to login into the frontend of the app and then assign the tickets to the agents he/she wishes to.</li>\n</ol>', 'Admin Account', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '2016-11-12 08:34:39', '', 181, 'http://127.0.0.1/181-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(966, 1, '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '<b>friedenstaucher</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\nis it possible to change the time format? I don’t need “2 days ago”. I want to show the real time/date like this “November 23, 2016 – 01:30 pm” for example…\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nWe don’t have a setting for this in the plugin, however we can edit/customize the plugin to achieve the desired result.\n\n<b>friedenstaucher</b>\n\n<b> </b>November 2016\n\ncan you tell me where I can edit this? I have bought the plugin with the username “werbekracher”... for your interests\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nNovember 2016\n\nCan you please create a ticket at : http://support.cssjockey.com/\n\nSo that i can share the required info with you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Time Format', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '2016-11-12 09:18:42', '', 183, 'http://127.0.0.1/183-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(967, 1, '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '<b>RobMason</b>\n\n<b>    </b>February 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHi, what’s the best way to remove the ‘Subject’ field from the new ticket form?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\n<b>    </b>February 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe best and easiest way would be to hide it using CSS but i would not recommend to remove the Subject field as it is required while submitting a new ticket and the ticket won’t get created if it is missing a required field like Subject.\n\nOther than that you would need to modify the plugin’s functionality and make the subject field not required and then remove it.\n\n<b>RobMason</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI wonder if you could help with that?\n\nI am also trying to remove the URL field (which I know is optional, but I want it removed entirely), but as none of your fields have classes I’m having trouble isolating it to hide with CSS.\n\nObviously I don’t want to change any of the plugin files, as I would like to keep it updated.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSorry for the delay in reply but here is the CSS to hide the URL field:\n\n.form-group label[for=”url”], input#url{ display:none !important; }\n\nLike i said before if we hide the Subject field the form will keep saying that is missing required field and it won’t get submitted, so it is not the right move to hide it using CSS.', 'To Remove the Subject Field', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'to-remove-the-subject-field', '', '', '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=40', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
(968, 1, '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '<b>RobMason</b>\n\n<b>    </b>February 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHi, what’s the best way to remove the ‘Subject’ field from the new ticket form?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\n<b>    </b>February 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe best and easiest way would be to hide it using CSS but i would not recommend to remove the Subject field as it is required while submitting a new ticket and the ticket won’t get created if it is missing a required field like Subject.\n\nOther than that you would need to modify the plugin’s functionality and make the subject field not required and then remove it.\n\n<b>RobMason</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI wonder if you could help with that?\n\nI am also trying to remove the URL field (which I know is optional, but I want it removed entirely), but as none of your fields have classes I’m having trouble isolating it to hide with CSS.\n\nObviously I don’t want to change any of the plugin files, as I would like to keep it updated.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSorry for the delay in reply but here is the CSS to hide the URL field:\n\n.form-group label[for=”url”], input#url{ display:none !important; }\n\nLike i said before if we hide the Subject field the form will keep saying that is missing required field and it won’t get submitted, so it is not the right move to hide it using CSS.', 'To Remove the Subject Field', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '967-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '2017-02-10 13:58:43', '', 967, 'http://127.0.0.1/967-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
