(969, 1, '2017-02-10 14:02:31', '2017-02-10 14:02:31', '<b>tedjoliman</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSupport, I have posted an urgent matter on your CSSJockey Support site, but I have not receive any response. Please advise.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>tedjoliman</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nLet me post it here to expedite the process and share with others.\n\nOur IP address looks like<a href="http://12.345.678.912:55580/"> http://12.345.678.912:55580/.</a> We can save all pages and settings except this plugin settings.\n\nIt keeps referring to<a href="http://_:55580/"> http://_:55580/.</a>\n\nOur server is behind a firewall and the Public IP is not from the server.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe have just posted a reply in your ticket and we can finish up with the debugging on our support portal as we may need info to access your site.\n\nWe will post here whatever solution we would find, so that others can benefit from it too.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>tedjoliman</b>\n\nFebruary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\ncjrupak,\n\nWe modified line 1096 on wp-content/plugins/cj-supportezzy/framework/framework.php and it works now.', 'Plugin Settings Error', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'plugin-settings-error', '', '', '2017-02-10 14:02:31', '2017-02-10 14:02:31', '', 0, 'http://gnosia.pauple.com/?post_type=pauple_helpie&amp;p=45', 0, 'pauple_helpie', '', 0),
