(994, 1, '2017-01-12 07:21:58', '2017-01-12 07:21:58', '<b>deharogroup</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\nThis is a pre-sale question. Is your plugin fully compatible with the Avada Theme? Just asking because I bought another plugin and the plugin wasn’t able to integrate into the My-Account section. If you would click on an order you wouldn’t see the option to report a problem with that order.\n\nAlso, does the client has the ability to submit a ticket from an existing order and the admin receive it and see which order the ticket is associated to?\n\nBasically what we need is a plugin that after the customer orders and receives the product, he can communicate with us in regard to that order if there was a problem and we can fix it for them.\n\nThanks in advance! It looks great. i just wanted to double check with you before buying it.', 'Enquiries on Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '125-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:21:58', '2017-01-12 07:21:58', '', 125, 'http://127.0.0.1/125-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(995, 1, '2017-01-12 07:23:42', '2017-01-12 07:23:42', '<b>BigBadBarry</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\n1: Can the the customer have multiple profiles?: i.e. one of my customers wants their manager to be able to see all support tickets their staff have raised to my company on my website\n\n2: Does this plugin send emailed when the support ticket is received / updated? if so, how customisable are these emails?\n\n3: How many customisable fields can be added to the form?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol>\n 	<li>The customer cannot have multiple roles. One role per user, he can create a separate login to manage another role.</li>\n 	<li>Yes, emails are send whenever there is a new ticket or a new reply to a ticket and when a ticket is closed. Email notifications content is fully customizable.</li>\n 	<li>You can add “n” number of customisable fields to the form.</li>\n</ol>\nTo know more follow this link :<a href="http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/"> http://docs.cssjockey.com/cjsupport/</a>\n\nTo try out our plugin before purchasing follow this link : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/">http://cssjockey.net/</a>', 'Multiple Profiles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:23:42', '2017-01-12 07:23:42', '', 128, 'http://127.0.0.1/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(996, 1, '2017-01-12 07:25:27', '2017-01-12 07:25:27', '<b>emanuel217</b>\n\n<b> </b>January 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWhy isn’t the demo site working in Internet Explorer (latest version) after logging in? Will I have the same problem if I buy the script?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAre you trying it on :<a href="http://cssjockey.net/"> http://cssjockey.net/</a> ?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>emanuel217</b>\n\n<b>    </b>January 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI am trying it on:<a href="http://preview.codecanyon.net/item/supportezzy-ticket-system/full_screen_preview/8908617?_ga=1.178585124.1414904881.1483384044"> http://preview.codecanyon.net/item/supportezzy-ticket-system/full_screen_preview/8908617?_ga=1.178585124.1414904881.1483384044</a>\n\nThis is the link in the “live preview” for the plugin.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\nOkay, we will check this but anyways we are working on a new version of this plugin from ground up with a new technology, so we will address any issues in this new version.\n\nIt should be available by the end of next month\n\n&nbsp;', 'Demo Sight Error', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '130-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:25:27', '2017-01-12 07:25:27', '', 130, 'http://127.0.0.1/130-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(997, 1, '2017-01-12 07:27:31', '2017-01-12 07:27:31', '<b>mara99</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\nCan all tickets, on the left side bar be hidden from the client, except the one that is created by the client himself?\n\nBy ‘Woocommerce’ integration do you actually mean that the client can make the payment for the support (and it will appear in his dashboard)?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe client will only see the ticket created by himself. All tickets will be only visible to the admin or if a ticket has been made public.\n\nBy WooCommerce we mean that all the products created under WooCommerce will be imported as the products for support, so that the client may choose which product he needs support for. It has nothing to do with payment.', 'Woocommerce Product Support', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:27:31', '2017-01-12 07:27:31', '', 132, 'http://127.0.0.1/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(998, 1, '2017-01-12 07:29:23', '2017-01-12 07:29:23', '<b>Soulfly999</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\nso it is possible to use this only with email adresses? Our user send us an email with the contact formular (formcraft) to a specific adress und then you could receive and answer the mail via Supportezzy?\n\n<b>cjrupak</b>\n\nJanuary 2017\n\nYes, this is possible with our IMAP feature. Try our plugin and IMAP feature by creating your own demo site at : <a href="http://cssjockey.net/">http://cssjockey.net/</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'IMAP Feature', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '135-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:29:23', '2017-01-12 07:29:23', '', 135, 'http://127.0.0.1/135-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(999, 1, '2017-01-19 04:26:30', '2017-01-19 04:26:30', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>jcev</strong></p>\nJanuary 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n<div class="comment__body">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, I purchased the plugin and i am having problems setting it up. When a ticket is submitted the submitter gets an email alert that it has been submitted, but us the ones assigned the ticket do not get the email.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container is-hidden"></div>\n<div class="js-comment comment__item-response">\n<div id="comment_11788225" class="comment__info">\n<div class="media">\n<div class="media__item"></div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30">\n<p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>CSSJockey </strong></p>\nJanuary 2016\n\n</div>\n<div class="media__body -align-center"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="comment__body--response">\n<div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">\n\nHi, Please create a ticket at <a href="http://support.cssjockey.com/" rel="nofollow">http://support.cssjockey.com</a> with temp WordPress admin account, so I can check the setup and help you with the fixes.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Email Error', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '472-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-19 04:26:30', '2017-01-19 04:26:30', '', 472, 'http://127.0.0.1/472-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
