(1161, 1, '2018-04-16 11:18:06', '2018-04-16 11:18:06', '<div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30"><p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfu3i29</strong></p></div><div class="media__body -align-center"><div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div></div><div class="comment__body"><div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">Any ETA on the new version and any list of planned new features available? - Will it possible to deactivate the creation of new accounts when new tickets are created from emails, i.e. to have them as “guest” tickets?</div></div><div class="js-comment comment__item-response"><div id="comment_13134121" class="comment__info"><div class="media"><div class="media__item">&nbsp;<br></div><div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30"><p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong>cfu3i29</strong></p></div><div class="media__body -align-center"><div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div><div>&nbsp;<br></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__body--response"><div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted"><br></div></div><div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container">&nbsp;<br></div></div><div class="js-comment comment__item-response"><div id="comment_13141111" class="comment__info"><div class="media"><div class="media__item">&nbsp;<br></div><div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30"><p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p>June 2016</div></div></div><div class="comment__body--response"><div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">The new version would still take at least another month. Probably in this month or by the end of next. List of new features will be rolled out after the development of the new version is completed, as we got many updates and new features and we will see which ones are most important and which ones can be released later under minor updates on a regular basis. But the features you have listed above will definitely be included in the upcoming version of the plugin.</div></div></div><div class="js-comment comment__item-response"><div id="comment_13568321" class="comment__info"><div class="media"><div class="media__item">&nbsp;<br></div><div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30"><p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cfu3i29">cfu3i29</a></strong></p></div><div class="media__body -align-center"><div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div><div>&nbsp;<br></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__body--response"><div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">Do you also have any plans to make it possible for users to access tickets created by email from different email addresses (i.e. separate user accounts for support users which allow multiple email addresses)? Reason: people often have more than one email address and don’t necessarily always use the one attached to their WP account.</div></div><div class="js-inject-target comment__action-container">&nbsp;<br></div></div><div class="js-comment comment__item-response"><div id="comment_13592889" class="comment__info"><div class="media"><div class="media__item">&nbsp;<br></div><div class="media__body -align-center -basis-30"><p class="t-body -weight-bold h-m0"><strong><a class="t-link -decoration-reversed" href="https://codecanyon.net/user/cjrupak">cjrupak</a></strong></p></div><div class="media__body -align-center"><div class="js-comment-tools comment__meta">June 2016</div><div>&nbsp;<br></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__body--response"><div class="js-comment__body t-preformatted">No plans to include this feature yet but we like the idea and we will try and make this possible down the road, as we proceed to elaborate this plugin and make it more and more flexible and customizable.</div></div></div>', 'ETA on the New Version', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '358-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-04-16 11:18:06', '2018-04-16 11:18:06', '', 358, 'http://127.0.0.1/358-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
